Commentary.Commentary: We are back for Bangladesh's inning. Shadman Islam and Mohammad Naim are the openers for Bangladesh. Tim Southee to start with the ball.

Bangladesh got the breakthrough in this session. Tom Latham scored 252 but then Mominul Haque got his wicket. Taskin Ahmed had a decent outing but failed to take a wicket. Shoriful Islam and Ebadot Hossain took two wickets each. Now it is time for their batters to hang in there as long as possible. Will New Zealand bowlers' will be lethal early on or the visitors will show their resilience. We will find out.

New Zealand have declared on 521/6. They were scoring quickly after the wicket of their captain and that suggested, the declaration was on the cards. A mammoth score for New Zealand and all credits to their skipper, Tom Latham, a brilliant innings from the local boy helps post a huge score. An important innings from Tom Blundell as well. He was looking sharp and was scoring in quick time. With contributions from Devon Conway and Will Young, the Kiwis feel they have enough runs to play with.
Short in length, on middle. Jamieson looks to pull but it takes the top edge and hits him on the helmet. The ball rolls over third slip and towards third man for a brace.
Very full, on middle. This is jammed out to long on for a single.
Length ball, way outside off. Tom Blundell throws the kitchen sink at it but misses.
Short, on middle, pulled away to deep square leg where the fielder shows his foot skills and stops it off his boot. Two.
FOUR! Full and on off. Tom Blundell drives it through covers for a boundary.
Full ball. Tom Blundell skips down and whips it to long on for a single. Fifty for Tom Blundell, comes at a quick rate.
Full and outside off. Kyle Jamieson drags it to long on for a single.
Full and on off, Blocked out.
On middle, drilled down to long on for a single.
Full again, on off, driven to long off for one run.
Full and angling on middle, pushed to long off for a single.
Another slower ball from Ahmed, this is pushed to point.
Full and on off. Kyle Jamieson keeps it out.
A full toss, way outside off, was a knuckle ball. Kyle Jamieson plays it late and hits it to covers.
A full toss, on middle, whipped to deep square leg for a single.
Length and outside off. Swing and a miss by Tom Blundell.
FOUR! Up and over! Length and on middle. Tom Blundell lifts it over mid off for a boundary.
On middle, this is pushed down to long on for one.
Full and on off. This is driven through covers for a brace. 500 up for New Zealand.
Kyle Jamieson walks out.

OUT! TAKEN! Tom Latham's inning comes to an end! All of the Bangladesh players' come towards him to appreciate his innings. The crowd is also on their feet to give around of applause. This is full and on middle. Tom Latham tries to go big again as he tries to slog-sweep it but gets a top edge to mid-wicket where Yasir Ali takes it.
Commentary.Howout: c Yasir Ali b Mominul Haque

Commentary.Commentary: SIX! 250 for Tom Latham, what a magnificent innings this is from the local boy! Full ball, on middle, Tom Latham slog-sweeps it over mid-wicket for a maximum.
FOUR! Cheeky! Full again. Tom Latham reverse sweeps it and beats short third man for a boundary.
SIX! HUGE! Full and on middle. Tom Latham skips down and hammers it to deep mid-wicket for a biggie.
On middle, Blocked out.
A slower ball, outside off. chopped to point.
Length and on off, tucked to mid-wicket.
Around off, this is punched through covers for a brace.
Short of a length, on off. Blocked out.
A low dipping full toss, outside off. Blundell squeezes it out to covers. Taskin Ahmed was trying the knuckle ball but failed to execute it.
Edged! A flighted ball, outside off. Latham rocks back and gets an outside edge to third man for a couple of runs to end the over.
Full and on off, pushed to long off for a single.
FOUR! Six boundaries for Tom Blundell now! Tossed up, on off. Blundell makes room and drives it through covers, beats the man there and it races away to the fence.
On middle, eased down to long on for a single.
This is outside off. Latham drags it wide of deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs. Latham had to hurry to the other end as he slipped while completing his run. Made in time though.
Full and on middle. Latham blocks it out.
The skipper, Mominul Haque is into the attack now!
Fuller, on off. Defended out on the front foot.
Around off. Blocked out.
FOUR! Wayward! Touch short, outside off. Tom Blundell arcs back and cuts it through point for a boundary. Taskin Ahmed is lacking consistency here.
Fuller, this one comes back in, on middle. Blundell is rock solid as he blocks this out. Good delivery, need to stick to this length.
Touch fuller, on off. Latham opens the bat face and steers it to third man for a single.
Fuller, on off. Blocked out.
Now a sweep, he is batting so smoothly here, Tom Latham! Fuller again, on middle, swept hard to deep square leg for a single. 11 coming off the over.
Fuller, slower and on middle. Tom Latham reverse sweeps it, hits it off the back of the bat to third man for a brace.
On middle, drilled down to long on for one.
FOUR! Runs coming at a fast rate now! Short ball, on off. Blundell punches off the back foot through covers for a boundary. Really good use of the feet.
Tom Blundell is busy on the pitch since he came on! He uses his feet and whips this wide of deep square leg for a brace.
Tossed up, on leg. Latham reverse sweeps it to deep point. One.
Good delivery and a good leave as well! Length ball, jagging in, outside off. Blundell shoulders arms to it.
FOUR! Punished! New Zealand will look to up the ante now in this passage of play! Tad short, on middle. Blundell pulls it through mid-wicket and that races away to the fence in flash.
Short of a length, on off. Defended out.
This one nips back in from outside off, on a length. Blundell gets on the front foot as he defends it under his eyes.
Length ball, angling across, outside off. Latham guides it to third man for a single.
Length and on off. Blocked out.
Taskin Ahmed is back on.
Full and straight, on middle. This is hit to short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Loose delivery! Short and way outside off. Tom Blundell cuts it hard and through point for a boundary. That also brings up 450 for New Zealand.
Full and outside off, pushed down to long off for a single.
Short ball, on middle. Latham rocks back and blocks it.
Fuller again. Blundell skips down and turns it to short mid-wicket who lets it through his hands for a single.
A single! Fuller and on middle. Latham sweeps it to fine leg for a single.
Single to end the over! Fuller and outside off, this is pushed to point for one.
On middle, tucked away to square leg for a single.
BEATEN AGAIN! This time the length was dragged back, outside off. Blundell hops and tries to push but gets beaten on the outside edge. Uneven bounce here.
BEATEN! A length ball, just outside off, extra bounce. Blundell has a poke away from the body but misses it.
Short in length, on middle. Blocked out.
Quick single! Full and on middle. Latham nudges it to mid-wicket and gets across for a single. A direct hit at the bowler's end but Latham was well in.
A huge appeal for LBW but nothing given! Short and angling on middle and leg. Blundell misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. That was sliding down.
This is full and just outside off. Kept out.
Uses his feet again as Blundell tucks it to mid-wicket.
On the pads, Blundell works it to the leg side.
Darted on the pads, flicked to square leg.
Very full, on middle, Blundell uses his feet as he flicks this to mid-wicket who makes a good stop.
Touch fuller, outside off. Latham offers no shot.
Full and outside off, pushed to covers.
Short of a length, on middle, tucked to mid-wicket for a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses.
FOUR! Crunched! A short ball, on middle. Blundell gets on top of the bounce and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Full, outside off. Left alone.
Good shot! A length ball, outside off. Blundell waits and punches off the back foot through cover-point for a brace. Timed it really well here.
On middle, drilled down to long on for a single.
Quicker one now, on middle. Blundell tucks it to short leg.
Top edge but safe! A loopy ball, on middle. Tom Latham looks to sweep it again but gets a leading edge towards short fine leg for a single.
Slightly short, on middle. Blundell punches it to mid-wicket for a single.
Darted on the pads, this is flicked to fine leg for a brace. Tom Blundell is off the mark.
Flighted ball, on middle, Latham sweeps it to fine leg for a single. Not much turn on offer for Mehidy Hasan.
Outside off, Left alone.
Shorter in length, on middle. Blundell keeps it out.
Short of a length, on middle. Blundell hops and blocks it.
This is way outside off. Blundell shoulders arms to it.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Full ball, angling on middle. Blundell squeezes it out to mid on.
Fuller ball, on middle. Defended off the front foot.
Hasan continues to serve it full. Latham solidly blocks it.
Tossed up again. Blocked out.
Tossed up, on off. Latham lunges and defends it.
FOUR! First runs after the break. Full and on middle. Latham whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Beats the diving fielder there.
Very full, flighted in the air and sliding down the leg side. Laham misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. An appeal for LBW but that was drifting down.
Who will bowl from the other end? It is Mehidy Hasan.
This one comes back in with the angle, outside off. Left alone.
A length ball, outside off. Blundell prods and defends it to point.

We are back for the post Lunch session. Both the umpires walk out to the field. They are followed by the players of Bangladesh. Tom Blundell will join Tom Latham in the middle. Shoriful Islam to resume his over.
... Day 2, Session 2 ...

The day though began with Conway’s ton and when he and Latham were batting, it seemed like the story of Day 1 is going to be repeated. However, a good piece of work in the field saw that partnership being broken. Taylor and Latham then put on another decent stand. Latham got up his double ton. Once Taylor fell though, Bangladesh have managed to slow the run rate and also gotten Daryl Mitchell and Henry Nicholls cheaply. They would want to continue this good work after the break. New Zealand on the other hand will probably up the ante and try and reach to that 500-run mark as soon as possible. A good session to cricket awaits. Do join us for the second session at 6:10 am IST (12:40 am GMT).

A decent session for Bangladesh compared to the ones yesterday! They are still well behind in the game but will be pleased with how they have fought on Day 2. Four wickets is what they managed and could have had 5, had Taskin Ahmed held onto the chance given by Latham.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Bangladesh end the session on a high! Shoriful Islam's hard work has been rewarded with a wicket. A length ball, outside off. Daryl Mitchell has a poke away from the body but the ball just nips slightly away and takes the outside edge to the keeper. Not sure why Daryl Mitchell took it upstairs as there was a noise. The review is wasted as the UltraEdge shows a spike as the ball passes the blade. That will be Lunch on Day 2.
Commentary.Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Shoriful Islam

Commentary.Commentary: Review taken! Daryl Mitchell takes a review after been given caught behind! There was definitely a sound there but Mitchell thinks it is off his pads. UltraEdge shows a spike off the outside edge.
Around off, on a length, punched to point for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Length and on off. Latham punches off the back foot to covers.
Tossed up, on off. Daryl Mitchell gets on the front foot to keep it out.
Angles it on middle, Blocked on the leg side.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
Good fielding! Short and outside off. Daryl Mitchell works it to point where the fielder dives to his right and stops it.
Quicker one, on middle, flicked to mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Tossed up, full and outside off.  Daryl Mitchell skips down and defends it out.
Mehidy Hasan is back into the attack.
On off, blocked.
Yet another delivery outside off, not played at.
Outside off, Latham shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! Up and over! This is short and wide outside off, Latham stands tall and cuts it over point for a boundary.
On middle, kept out.
Daryl Mitchell walks down the wicket! This is bowled shorter and on the pads, he looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. It rolls on the leg side for one. Leg bye.
Back of a length and on off, Latham keeps it out.
Back of a length and on off, Latham defends.
Daryl Mitchell is off the mark! On off, this is pushed to covers for one.
Angled into middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
Daryl Mitchell walks out to bat!

OUT! There is a spike as the ball passes the bat and Bangladesh have got another one. Ebadot Hossain gets his second and Henry Nicholls bags a duck, his poor form continues. This is on a length and around off, this lands and then jags back in. It goes off something to the keeper who takes it and appeals. The umpire shakes his head. Mominul Haque takes the review. Replays show that it is off the inside edge. A good little passage of play here for the visitors.
Commentary.Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Ebadot Hossain

Commentary.Commentary: Review time! A huge appeal for a caught behind but turned down! Bangladesh review. It has hit something but not sure if it is bat or pad.
Another short one to end, Latham ducks.
Another bumper, Latham lets it go over him.
Bangs it short and on middle, defended.
A good short one, Latham ducks under it.
WIDE! Way too short, goes over the batter's head. Wided.
Extra bounce! The surface seems to have spiced up! New Zealand won't mind this! Shorter and on middle, Latham looks to defend but this one takes off and hits the splice.
A good bumper, ducked under.
Short and on the body, this is pulled towards deep square leg for one.
On middle, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off, left alone.
BEATEN! There is still something in this wicket for the seamers! Fuller and around off, this lands and moves away. Latham looks to drive but is beaten.
Solid! On off, defended.
BEATEN! Very nicely bowled! On off and angling away. Henry Nicholls looks to defend but is beaten. Good over by Taskin.
A single as this is played on the off side.
Short and down the leg side, left alone.

DROPPED! A good effort by Taskin but such chances need to be taken when you are behind in the game! Short and on middle, this one holds in the surface. Latham looks to flick but closes the face of the bat early. It goes off the leading edge, lobs on the wicket, Taskin runs in and dives forward, gets two hands to it but spills it.
Down the leg side, Latham looks to flick but misses.
Shorter and on the body, ducked under.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length and on off, defended.

OUT! TAKEN! Ross Taylor has been dismissed and this could well be the final walk off in whites for Ross Taylor for the Kiwis. The whole crowd is on their feet to applaud one of their best. A soft dismissal. This is angled into the pads, Taylor looks to flick it but it goes more off the inner half and Shoriful Islam takes it at square leg. Taylor was looking to be aggressive throughout his innings and falls in that process. Henry Nicholls walks out to bat.
Commentary.Howout: c Shoriful Islam b Ebadot Hossain

Commentary.Commentary: Outside off, Taylor slashes but does not connect.
Another one on the stumps, kept out.
On middle, defended.
Top edge but safe! Shorter and on middle, Latham pulls, it goes off the top edge but wide of deep square leg for two.
WIDE! Way too short, Latham lets it go over him. Wided.
On off, defended towards cover for one.
Goes short this time and on off, Taylor looks to pull but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On off, Taylor plays it to covers.

FOUR! Catch it is the call but that is in the gap! Outside off, Taylor slashes hard at it, it goes off the outside edge, between gully and first slip. Races down towards third man. There is a fielder there but he has no chance. Another fortunate boundary for the Kiwis.
Angled into the pads, Taylor works it through square leg for one.
Slighty shorter in length, some extra bounce too. Taylor rides on top of it and plays it towards point for one.
Back of a length and on off, Taylor pushes it to covers.
On off, Ross plays it back to the bowler.
On off, Taylor plays it back to the bowler.
Well bowled! Goes wide of the crease and angles it into the off pole. Lands and gets it to shape away. Taylor pushes at it and gets beaten.
Back of a length and on off, Taylor defends.

DRINKS! New Zealand continue to strengthen their grip on this game! The day began with Conway getting to his ton. He though soon was dismissed courtesy some brilliance in the field by Mehidy Hasan. Latham though continued along with Taylor. The skipper got his double ton up and the two have taken New Zealand's score to 400. More of the same is what the Kiwis would want. Bangladesh on the other hand, have been a lot better with their lines and lengths this morning but there is not a lot to show in the wicket column for the bowlers. They would hope this break works in their favor.

Outside edge but another run! 400 up for the Kiwis! On a length and around off, this one holds its line. Taylor looks to block, it goes off the outside edge past first slip and down towards third man for one.
Good length and on off, Taylor hangs back and defends it onto the ground.
On off, Latham pushes it through covers for one.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
On off, Taylor plays it to point for one.
NO BALL! Edgy run! Outside off and on a length. Latham looks to push at it, it goes off the outside edge past gully and down to deep backward point for one. Taskin has overstepped.
On off, defended.
Angled into the pads, Latham works it through square leg and takes one.
BEATEN! This one lands on off and slants away. Latham is beaten as he tries to block.
Angled into the pads, Taylor works it through mid-wicket for one.
Two more! Angled into the pads, Taylor works it fine and takes two towards fine leg.

FOUR! That is a gift and it is put away! Full and on off, Taylor leans into this one and creams it through extra cover. The man at mid off moves to his left and does put in a dive but his effort goes in vain.
On off, defended well.
Fuller and on middle, this is played back to the bowler.
Third leave in a row as Taskin bowls it outside off again.
Another one outside off, not played at.
Outside off, Latham does not fiddle with it.

FOUR! Classy! What a shot to get your double ton up! In front of his home crowd, the skipper has led from the front. Everyone here is on their feet applauding what has been a fine, fine effort. A game which the Kiwis have to win and the skipper steps up. This is by no means a half volley, on a length and around off, Latham times it through covers for a boundary.
Good length and on off, Latham looks to defend, it goes off the inner half towards mid-wicket. They think of a run for a second but then decide not to go for it.
Angled into the pads, this is worked towards mid-wicket for one. He moves onto 199 and keeps strike.
FOUR! 31st boundary for Latham and he moves to 198! Short and on the body, Latham pulls it fine. Fine leg runs to his left and dives but he has no chance.
Outside off, Latham shoulders arms to this one.
Angled into the pads, this is worked towards square leg for one.
Outside off, easy leave.
On off, Taylor stands tall and keeps it out.
Taylor takes one now! On off, this is pushed to point for one.
A sinlge now! Back of a length and on off, Latham pushes it through covers for one.
Shorter and on off, this time he makes the batter play, Latham hangs back and defends.
Three leaves in a row then! Once again angling it away from off, not played at.
Wider this time outside off, easy leave.
Starts off with a good length ball around off, angling away. Left alone.
Change! Taskin Ahmed is on!
Make that 4 then! So a good comeback by Shoriful Islam after going for that boundary! Length and on off, Taylor plays it to covers.
Three good deliveries on the trot by Shoriful Islam! On off, Taylor blocks it.
Again, attacks the stumps, Taylor gets behind the line of the delivery and keeps it out.
Angles it into the off pole now, Taylor blocks.
FOUR! Trademark Ross Taylor! A shot which has given him a lot of runs! Short and outside off, Taylor cuts it through point, this one races away to the fence.
On the, Taylor keeps it out.
On the stumps, defended.
On the pads now, Taylor follows the boundary with a single as he works it on the leg side.

FOUR! That is beautiful! What a shot from Taylor to get off the mark! This is not a bad delivery, it is on a length and around off, Taylor pushes it on the up through covers and this one races away to the fence.
Tap and run! Back of a length and on off, Latham plays it to point and takes one. Gets Taylor on strike. Ebadot Hossain got him in the last game, can he get him here too?
Very full and on middle, Latham strokes it back to the bowler.
More runs in that third man region! Good length and on off, Latham looks to defend, this goes more off the outer half for two in that area.
A maiden then! Just outside off from around the wicket. Left alone.
Shorter and on the body, ducked under.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length and on off, kept out nicely.
On off, blocked.
Ross Taylor walks out to bat in what could well be his last innings for New Zealand! A guard of honor for him from the Bangladesh players as he makes his way to the middle.

OUT! RUN OUT! Conway is short and this is probably the kind of spark Bangladesh needed. These two just did not look like getting out and a run out was probably the only way this partnership could have been broken. A slight hesitation costs Conway and ends a brilliant knock from him. On off, Latham looks to drop and run. There is a small hesitation but they go for it. Mehidy Hasan gets to the all, picks it up and with a dive forward, hits the stumps at the striker's end. It is taken upstairs and replays show that Conway is short. Can Bangladesh build from here now?
Commentary.Howout: run out (Mehidy Hasan)

Commentary.Commentary: A run out appeal and it is taken upstairs! Bangladesh are celebrating!
Back of a length and on off, defended.
Back of a length and on off, Conway plays it to covers.
On the stumps, Conway stays back and defends.
Classy! Back of a length and on off, this is pushed through covers for two.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On middle, defended.
Some nice movement and bounce but after passing the batter! Outside off, this one comes back in. Extra bounce and it moves back in after passing the batter. The keeper takes it to his right.
On middle, kept out.
FOUR! Latham is now just the 10 runs short of a double ton! Short and wide outside off, this is cut over point for  a boundary. His 30th boundary in this innings.
Back of a length, this one jags back in. Latham looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Outside off, Latham does not fiddle with it.
Back of a length and on off, :Latham defends it to covers.
A testing over comes to an end! On the stumps, Conway keeps it out.
On middle, Conway works it to mid-wicket.
On the pads, Conway looks to flick but misses. He gets hit on the pads.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one on the stumps, blocked.
On off, on a length. Kept out nicely.
Just outside off, not played at. End of a maiden.
On middle, Latham plays it to mid on.
On off, defended.
Now bowls this one outside off, left alone.
Left on length! On off, this is a back of a length ball. It comes back in. Latham is hit high on the pads.
Starts off with a loosener! Down the leg side, Latham looks to flick but misses.
Shoriful Islam to bowl from the other end.
A dot to end but 8 from the over! On off, defended.

FOUR! Up and over! Fortunate boundary! Length and on off, this one moves away and takes off after landing. Conway looks to defend but this goes off the shoulder of the bat and over the slip cordon for a boundary. The runs continue to flow.
Another one on off, defended.
On the stumps, blocked.
Outside off, angling away. Left alone.

FOUR! 100 for Devon Conway! His third in Tests and he just continues to score big runs. A special knock from a very solid player. An innings full of class and composure. A gift is what he gets to reach the milestone. Full and on the pads, he works it fine and this one races away to the fence. Now he will be eyeing to make this a big one.

We are all set for the action to begin! Tom Latham and Devon Conway walk out to resume their innings. Devon Conway is a run away from a ton. He will take strike and will be facing Ebadot Hossain. Here we go...

The visitors however, will be quite demoralised. They might have come into this game with tremendous confidence but the way the Kiwis batted would have surely deflated the morale of the visiting side. After electing to bowl, 349 runs is not what you would want to be conceding in a day and that too picking just the one wicket. They need to remember the fact though that they did trigger a collapse in the first innings of the first game. Can they do so again? They will have to or they’ll have close to 0 percent chances of winning this game. An important first session awaits.

A stellar show with the bat by the New Zealand skipper and Devon Conway has put the Kiwis in an extremely commanding position. They have a lot of time in their hand and will be looking for a massive first innings score. Are we going to see yet another superb batting display from the Kiwis or do Bangladesh have a fight back in store?
... Day 2, Session 1 ...

Bangladesh will probably be rueing the fact that they elected to bowl. They were fooled by the amount of grass on the wicket but there was hardly any assistance from the surface. Also, the bowling wasn’t all that great. They failed to hit the right lines and lengths on regular occasions and due to that, they are well behind in the game. Getting back into this game is going to be a big task. They need wickets and in heaps on Day 2 and it will be interesting to see if they do manage to fight back. Do join us for Day 2 on Monday, 10th January at 3:30 am IST (10 pm GMT, previous day). Till then, you can catch the action of the Ashes as England are fighting hard to salvage a draw. Till then, Cheers!

Tom Latham was the highlight but Devon Conway too played a delightful knock. The platform though was set by the opening stand as they added 148. Will Young also looked all set for a big score but he fell. Conway and Latham then batted, batted and batted. The two have built a 200-run stand. Latham is eyeing a double ton whereas Conway is one short of his hundred. Also, the rate New Zealand have scored at is quite incredible and they have enough time now to post a huge total and that is what they’ll be eyeing.

A day thoroughly dominated by the Kiwis! Tom Latham wanted to make a statement after their surprise loss in the last game and he has led from the front. A scintillating knock has seen his side on course to bat the visitors out of the game.
Full ball, on middle. Latham prods and defends this out. That will be Stumps on Day 1.
On middle. Blocked out. Devon Conway has to wait for his century a bit longer.
Full and on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Turn for Hasan! This lands on middle and turns away. Latham prods and defends it off the outer half.
Around off, this is drilled down to long off for a single. Conway on 99 now.
A flighted ball, on off. Conway drives it hard bit straight to covers.
Mehidy Hasan to bowl the final over.
On middle, on a length. Blocked out.
On middle, this is hit to mid-wicket.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Short and on middle. Latham sits under it.

OVERTHROWS! We have seen so many today by Bangladesh! Angles it on the pads. Latham misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. A quick leg bye as it rolls to square leg. An over throw as the fielder misses his shy at the keeper's end. Two leg byes. The partnership races to 200 now.
Length and outside off. Conway taps it late and towards point for a quick single. He moves to 98.
FOUR! EDGED AND FOUR! A length ball, outside off. Latham tries to defend it with soft hands but gets an outside edge through gully and towards the third man fence. He moves to 186.
Fuller ball, angling on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Length ball, shaping away, outside off. Latham shoulders arms to it.
On middle, on a length. Blocked out.
Three taken! On a length, outside off. Devon Conway opens the bat face and guides it through the gully region for three runs as the fielder chases it and flicks it back in time.
Length and on off. Blocked out.
FOUR! The sound it made off the bat! Beautiful! Pitches it up, outside off. Latham drives it crisply through covers for a boundary.
Length, on middle, this is flicked to square leg.
A full ball, outside off. Latham pushes it and beats mid off for a couple of runs.
Fuller ball, outside off. Left alone.
A full ball, outside off, a late outswinger here as the keeper had to make a full-stretched dive to his left to collect it. Almost in front of first slip.
Length ball, angling across, outside off. Latham covers his off stump and lets it through.
Much better! Full, on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Full ball, outside off. Conway offers no shot. Bangladesh are not using the new ball effectively as they are bowling way outside off.
This is way outside off. Left alone.
A hint of outswinger but the length was too full, pushed to mid on.
Targets the stumps, on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Starts from around the wicket, on a length, outside off. Conway punches it to cover.
Shoriful Islam is back into the attack.
On middle, this is hit to square leg.
Leg bye! An appeal for LBW but not given! A length ball, it lands on off and nips back in. Conway hops and looks to flick but gets hit high on the pads. A leg bye.
FOUR! Elegance! A full ball, outside off. Conway gets on the front foot and drives it through covers for a boundary. He moves to 94.
This one shapes back in, on middle, fuller ball. Conway toe ends it to the leg side.
Length and on off. Latham taps it to point for a quick single.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Bangladesh have taken the new ball. Also, Taskin Ahmed is back on.
Sliglty short, on off, punched to covers for a single.
FOUR! Another expensive over for Bangladesh! Full and on middle. Latham comes down the track and lofts it over mid off for a boundary.
Short and quick, on middle, drilled down to long on for a single.
Again reverse sweeps it but straight to point.
Now reverse sweeps this full ball to point.
FOUR! In the air and in the gap! A full ball, on middle. Conway slog-sweeps it, not quite off the middle, but bisects the square leg and mid-wicket for a boundary.
Short of a length, on off. Conway knocks it to point for a single. 11 coming off this over. Will Bangladesh take the new ball? Not yet!
Short ball, angling down, pulled away to deep square leg for a couple.
FOUR! Ebadot Hossain continues to leak runs! Short and on off. Devon Conway punches it with soft hands, with an angled bat and it races away to the point fence.
On off, Blocked out.
FOUR! Nicely played! Full ball, on the pads. Conway whips it through the diving square leg fielder for a boundary.
Length and on off. Conway is hurried to his pull shot, to mid-wicket.
On off, Defended out.
Fuller ball, on middle, swept to square leg for a single.
Short and on off. Conway punches off the back foot through covers for a brace.
Short, on off. Blocked it.
On middle. Blocked out.
Lovely bowling! This one comes with the angle, full and around leg. Conway shuffles and looks to reverse sweep it but misses it completely.
Around off, on a length. Latham pushes it to mid off.
Conway is hurried through! Length and on middle. This is hit to square leg for a single.
Full, on middle, this is nudged to square leg for one more.
On middle, Conway looks to drive but gets an inside edge to mid-wicket for a single. 300 up for New Zealand.
Another solid defense from Devon Conway.
A length ball, on off. Conway defends it away from the body.
The new ball is due. Will Bangladesh take it? The answer is NO, for now.
Full and on off. Latham blocks it out.
On off, Kept out.
Review taken! There was definitely a sound but UltraEdge shows no spike on it. Bangladesh lose their review.

NOT OUT! A full ball, outside off, this one lands and spins away. Tom Latham prods to defend but seems to miss it. The keeper collects it and appeals for it straightaway, nothing from the umpire though. There was a sound there and Bangladesh take the review. UltraEdge shows nothing and Tom Latham survives.
On middle, eased down to long on for a single.
Full and on off. Latham dances down and pushes it to mid off for a single. 150 of the partnership between these two.
Tossed up, on middle. Blocked out.
Mehidy Hasan is brought back into the attack.
Touch fuller, outside off. Conway gets behind the line of the ball and defends it out.
On the hips, this is flicked to square leg for a single.
Drags his length back and serves it short. Latham offers no shot.
Length, on middle. this is defended out.
Another short ball, on middle. Latham ducks underneath.
WIDE! Bangs a short ball, on middle. Latham sits under it and the umpire signals a wide.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Leg bye! On the pads, Latham misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. It rolls to square leg for a leg bye.
Length ball, angling on middle, pushed to mid on. A fumble there and the batters try to steal a single but settle against it.
Short ball now, on middle. Latham evades it.
Tap and run! Good running between the wickets! On a length, on off. Conway hops and taps it in front of point for a quick single.
On off. Blocked out.
Short of a length, outside off. Latham guides it to backward point for an easy single.
Ebadot Hossain (18-1-98-0) is back on.
Changes the angle as Ahmed comes around the wicket, full and outside off. Blocked out off the front foot.
Around off. Defended out.
FOUR! Edged and races away! Length ball, angling outside off. Conway looks to cut but it takes the outside edge and races over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Length, on off, this is punched to short cover.
Length ball, just outside off. Conway shoulders arms to it.
Length ball, slanting outside off, pushed to point.
DRINKS! Yet another dominating passage for New Zealand. Both the batters are settled and Conway is all set to reach yet another century. Wickets are much needed for Bangladesh.
Full ball, on middle. Pushed back to the bowler.
Slower, short and outside off. Conway steers it down with an angled bat to backward point for three runs. Good running.
Gives air to this one, full and on off. Conway is early to his flick and gets a soft leading edge back to the bowler.
Full, on middle. Latham comes down the track and bunts it to long on for a single.
Now a back foot drive to covers for a single.
On middle, this is worked to square leg for a single.
This one straightens off the deck. Conway gets an inside edge to the leg side.
Very full, on middle. Blocked out.
Slight turn now, outside off, this is guided to point.
On middle, Latham skips down and drills it to long on for a single.
Flatter and outside off, this is hit to point for a single.
Fuller, this one skids through. Conway drives but gets an inside edge to mid-wicket.
Three dots to follow to finish the over, A loopy ball, on off, Defended out solidly.
Fuller, on middle, pushed to silly mid on.
Tossed up, on middle, Blocked out.
On middle, flicked to square leg for a single. Three singles of three balls so far.
Another single as this is hit to covers.
Full ball, on off. Conway drives it more off the outer half to covers for a single.
Full and on middle. Latham prods and blocks it.
On middle, drilled down to long on for a single.
Edgy runs! Fuller ball, on off. Latham looks to defend but it goes off the splice to third man for a single.
Short and outside off, cut away to deep point for a single.
Full and outside off. Blocked out.
A full ball, this one drifts in. Conway looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the back pad.
Dot to finish the over! Short and on off, hit back to the bowler.
Full and on middle, this is drilled down to long on for a single.
Fuller and on off. Latham prods and pushes it to point for a single.
Slightly quicker now, Blocked out.
Easy single! Darted on the pads, flicked to square leg now for one.
On middle, nudged to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Single to end the over! Short and on off. Latham punches it to deep cover for a single.
Full and on middle, swept to deep square leg for one more.
Flighted, on middle. Blocked out.
Tap and run! Short and angling across, outside off. Latham punches it to point for a single.
Tossed up, on off. Kept out.
Full ball, on off, this is pushed back to Hasan.
Uppishly but safe! Short again, on off. Conway pushes it aerially back to Shanto who dives to his right and takes it on a bounce.
Shorte, drifting on middle. Conway punches off the back foot to covers.
Full and on off. Latham pushes it to long off for one.
This is hit back to the bowler.
Full ball, outside off. Conway drives it to deep point for a single.
Slower and outside off, this is pushed to covers off the back foot.
Najmul Hossain Shanto is into the attack now.

FIFTY for Devon Conway! He looks in fine form after coming back from the injury! Already a century to his name, can he convert this one as well? On the pads, this is flicked to square leg for a single.
This is hit to silly mid off.
FOUR! Comes over the wicket to the left-hander. This is full and on middle. Conway pre-meditates and reverse sweeps it to point for a boundary. One shy of fifty.
Tossed up, outside off, this is driven to long off for a single.
Gives more flight to this one. Defended.
Full and on off. Latham gets on the front foot to block it.
Short of a length, on off. Latham pulls it to deep mid-wicket and keeps the strike.
Length,on off. Conway guides it through point for one more.
Quicker one now, on off. Blocked out.
Length and on off, this is punched off the back foot to point for a single.
Short in length, on middle, pulled to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller ball, outside off. Conway leaves it.
Fuller ball and this is drilled down to long on for one more.
On middle, eased down to long on for a single.
Tossed up, full, spins away after landing. Latham looks to sweep it across but misses.
Slightly short, on off, punched to covers.
Tossed up, on middle. Latham gets on the front foot to defend.
Full and outside off, pushed to covers.
Good length and on off, defended.
Short and on middle, Latham pulls, it is uppish but lands safe in the square leg region for one.
Shorter and on middle, Latham hangs back and blocks.
Outside off, an easy leave.
Goes short again and on off, Latham watches it go through to the keeper.
A short one and on middle, Latham sways out of the way.
Angled into the pads, Latham works it through square leg for one.
On middle, defended.
A single this time as this is pushed down to long on.
Quicker and on off, Conway looks to defend it late, it hits the inside edge and goes on the leg side.
On off, this is blocked.
A huge appeal but not given! Review too not taken! Tossed up full and outside off, Conway looks to play the reverse sweep but misses. He hits the ground in the process. A huge appeal but nothing.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! 150 up for Latham! The crowd here is on their feet to applaud what has been a brilliant knock. Just the 199 balls to get to that milestone and does so in stlye! On the pads, he times it through mid-wicket. It races away to the fence.
Goes fuller and outside off, Latham shoulders arms to this one.
Yet another delivery outside the off pole, not played at again.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Put away! Short and outside off, Latham slashes at it, he getsi it behind point for yet another boundary. He just a boundary away from his 150.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to square leg for one.
On the stumps, defended.
Close! This one lands outside off, Latham is not sure whether to play at it or not, in the end he pokes at it, he gets an inside edge which lands between his legs and goes behind to the keeper.
On the stumps, this one turns away a little. Latham plays it to covers.
Floats it up on off, defended.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
Two dots to end but 7 from the over! On off, Conway guides it to point.
Good length and on off, Conway defends it out.
Takes one now! Shorter and on off, this is guided through point for one.

EDGY FOUR! Finds the third man fence! Latham is scoring really quickly here, yes, he has been fortunate but he is being brave! Shorter in length and outside off, Latham guides it uppishly but past gully and into the third man fence.
Hit hard but only for one! Short and outside off, Conway plays it through point for one.
Drop and run! On off, Latham stands tall and plays it on the off side for a quick single.
Latham now takes one as he pushes it down to long off.
Fuller and on off, this is eased down to long off for one.
On the stumps, defended.
On middle, kept out.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Fires it on the stumps, defended.
Length and on off, Conway defends it onto the ground with soft hands.
Outside off, Conway shoulders arms to this one.
A little too straight, Latham misses out. He tries to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls on the leg side. A leg bye taken.
Short and outside off, left alone.
On a length, just outside off, Latham guides it to point.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
A single to end! Slightly short, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Outside the line of off! Hasan maybe expected Latham to play the sweep, he fires it full and outside off. Latham does look to sweep but misses to get hit on the pad.
Quicker and on off, Latham works it to mid-wicket.
On middle, defended.

That is quite unlucky! This is tossed up on off, Latham looks to play the paddle sweep but this goes off the top edge, the fielder at slip runs towards the leg side. This though goes over him and towards fine leg for two.
On middle, Conway works it towards mid on for one.
A dot to end but the damage was done earlier. Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! Just over! Latham is in some touch here! Back-to-back boundaries for him! Short and on off, Latham guides it just over the leaping gully fielder for a boundary. Runs are flowing after the break too.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Superb control! Short and on middle, Latham stands tall, gets on top of the bounce and pulls it through square leg. There is a fielder in the deep but he has no chance.
Another single as Conway gets one on his pad and he works it to fine leg.
Angled into the pads, Latham looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and goes towards fine leg. A leg bye taken.
Outside off, it is an easy leave.
On middle, Conway defends.
A loud shout but there is bat! Conway looks to play the reverse again, this one is quite full and on middle, he gets an underedge onto the pads.

FOUR! Really good shot! Bangladesh just can't keep it tight at the moment or we should say the Kiwis are not letting the bowlers settle. The reverse sweep is out and it is played brilliantly through backward point for a boundary.
Shorter and on off, Conway pushes it to covers.
Loopy ball on middle, this is worked to mid on.
Short and outside off, Conway cuts but to point.
A leg bye to end! On the pads, this is nudged around the corner for one, it came off the pads. Leg bye given.
Half an appeal but turned down! Shorter and outside off, Conway looks to pull but misses, it hits the body and goes to the keeper. The bowler appeals for a catch but turned down.
Islam goes short and on middle, this is pulled hard through mid-wicket. Two taken.
That is a beauty! This is angled into the off pole, it lands and then moves away. Conway looks to defend but is beaten.
Good length and on off, this one shapes away. It is guided to point.
Two more! Runs continue to come for the Kiwis! On off, Conway pushes it through covers for two.
Shoriful Islam to bowl from the other end.
A loopy ball, on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Full ball, outside off. Latham again tries to sweep but misses.
FOUR! In the gap! Nice way to start the final session! Fuller again, on middle, this is swept hard to deep square leg for a boundary.
Full and way outside off. Left alone.
A full ball, on middle. Conway sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Tossed up, full and on off, Defended out.
We are back for the final session. Tom Latham and Devon Conway stride out to continue their innings. Mehidy Hasan has the ball in his hands.
... Day 1, Session 3 ...

Bangladesh were poor with the ball, their fielding also was way below-par. Too many overthrows and lack of consistency have allowed New Zealand to dominate the session. To add to that, they were quite unlucky too and not a lot has gone their way. They need wickets quickly after the break or there will be possibility of them being batted out of the match. Will we see a fight back? Stay tuned for find out.

Another session credited to New Zealand. Tom Latham and Devon Conway have stitched a partnership of 50 and both are looking solid on the crease. The skipper, Tom Latham continued his dominance from the morning session and got his century in style. Will Young was also looking good as he got his fifty but then one false shot saw him walk back to the pavilion. Devon Conway joined his skipper into the middle and he is looking in good touch so far.
Length and on off. Latham hops and blocks it out. That will be Tea on Day 1.
Keeps bowling on a length, on off. Latham defends it on the leg side.
Angles across a length ball, on off. Defended out.
A length ball, on middle, tickled to deep backward square leg for a single.
Outside off, on a length. Conway offers no shot.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Short and outside off, this is cut away to deep point for a single.
A loopy ball, on off. Defended off the front foot.
Flights this one, on off. Conway looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Tossed up, outside off. Blocked out.
Fuller and on off, driven to covers.
Darted on the pads, this is flicked to square leg for a single. 200 up for New Zealand.
Much better over from Taskin Ahmed! This is full and outside off. Conway misses his drive. An appeal follows for caught behind but was more of an optimistic one.

A huge appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. Mominul Haque is also not interested to review it. A length ball, nipping back in, around off. Conway leans and looks to defend and gets hit high on the pads, no foot movement from Conway.
Around off, on a length. Blocked out.
A length ball, on off. Conway defends it towards point. Good from Taskin sticks to the same length and does not allow Conway to rotate the strike.
A length ball, on middle. Blocked out.
On a length, on off. Conway blocks it under his eyes.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Short, slower and way outside off. Latham slaps it to the right of point for a boundary. That also brings up 50 of the partnership between these two.
Short again, on off. Latham blocks it off the back foot.
Another single as this is worked to square leg by Conway.
This is very full, on middle. Latham pre-meditates and sweeps it on the leg side for a single.
Slightly short, on off. Latham rocks back and punches it off the back foot through point for a couple.
Tossed up, full and on off, pushed to bowler.
On a length, on middle, Conway hits it to mid-wicket.
Too easy for Latham! Ahmed is lacking consistency and not piling any pressure! On middle, this is tucked away to square leg for a single.
WIDE! A pacy short ball, on middle. Latham sits under it. The keeper collects it over his head.
Fuller and on off, this is pushed to mid off.
On the pads, this is flicked to deep square leg for a single.
On a length, on middle, extra pace here. Conway hops and blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! EDGED! Ahmed creates an angle as he comes around the wicket. This is full and on middle. Conway looks to defend but gets an outside edge, through the slip cordon for yet another edgy boundary.
Taskin Ahmed is back into the attack.
On middle. Blocked out, this one drifts back in but Latham is strong with his wrists.
Fuller and outside off, this is pushed to covers.
Flatter ball, outside off. Left alone.
A loopy ball, on middle. Latham hits it on the leg side.
Fuller now, on middle. Blocked out.
Shorter, drifting in, outside off. Latham has his stumps covered as he leaves this one.
FOUR! No need to run for that! Frustration increases for Ebadot Hossain! Fuller ball, on off. Conway punches it this time, through mid off for a boundary.
Three taken! Pitches it up, on off. Latham drives it through mid off. Mominul Haque gives a chase and does well to flick it back and save a single for his team. The replay confirms the same.
Hossain continues to bowl in outside off line. Latham is not interested to play it.
Easy leave as this is outside off.
This one shapes back in, on a length, outside off. Latham covers his stumps and lets it through.
Length ball, outside off. Latham shoulders arms.
Through the legs! This is short, angling on middle, quicker as well. Latham gets on the back foot and gets an inside edge through the legs to fine leg for a single.
Tossed up, outside off. Defended out.
Full ball, on middle. Latham looks to sweep but mistimes it on the leg side.
A loopy ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Full again, this is hit back to Hasan who misfields and allows a single. Too easy for New Zealand right now, no signs of any pressure.
Fuller and outside off, pushed to covers.
Ouchh! That might hurt! Good seam movement here! On a length, on middle. Tom Latham is squared up as he looks to defend and gets hit on the box.
Full ball, on middle, Conway flicks it awkwardly to square leg for a single.
A short ball, outside off, this is cut through point for a single.
Fuller and slanting across, outside off. Latham leaves it alone.
Length and outside off. Left alone.

FOUR! EDGED! Tom Latham riding his luck here! A length ball, outside off, the ball holds it line. Latham looks to defend but gets an outside edge and it falls just short of second slip. The ball bounces and races away to the fence.
Fuller and on off, pushed to cover.
Top edge but safe! A full ball, on middle. Devon Conway looks to slog-sweep but gets a top edge over short fine leg for a couple of runs.
A flighted ball, on middle. Conway jams it out on the leg side.
Short ball, given more air, outside off. Conway is early as he tries to push and hits it just short of covers.

CENTURY for Latham! The local boy enjoys the applause from the crowd as the captain anchors the innings with intensity. Wonderful innings from the skipper! This is full and on middle, flicked to square leg for a single. Skipper leading from the front.
Tossed up, on middle. Blocked out.
Overpitched, on middle. This is flicked to square leg.
Fuller ball on 136 clicks. Conway is early to his drive as this is hit to mid on.
On middle, on a length. Blocked out.
This one comes quickly to Conway who gets his bat down in time to defend.
Full and on middle, clipped to square leg.
Tom Latham on 99! On a length, on middle, extra bounce. A soft leading edge as it rolls to covers. Single.
A flatter ball, drifting in, around off. Conway gets low to defend but gets a thick inside edge onto the pads. The ball lobs just away of first slip.
Short and on middle. Latham tucks it off the back foot to square leg. One.
A flighted ball, on off, pushed to mid on for a single.
Short and on off. Conway keeps it out.
SIX! New Zealand not letting Mehidy Hasan settle in! Fuller and on middle. Conway reaches to the pitch of the ball and tonks it well over long on for a biggie.
Tossed up, on middle. Latham skips down and smacks it to long on for a single. Moves to 97 now.
Length and outside off. Devon Conway offers no shot to it.
Another solid block from Conway.
Around off. Blocked out.
An appeal for LBW but not given! A length ball, around off, it jags back in and hits high on the pads to Conway as he looks to defend. Height might have saved him.
On middle, on a length. Defended out.
Length and on off. Blocked out.
Quicker, flatter and on off. Latham rocks back and defends it out.
Shorter and on off. Blocked out.
Again this is pushed to mid off by Latham.
Good running from New Zealand, keeping the pressure on the bowling side. Around off, this is pushed to mid off for a quick single.
Angles it on middle, this is flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller and on middle, pushed to silly mid on.
This is way outside off. Left alone.
Length and on middle, nudged to square leg for a single.

In the air but safe! Fair to say it is Tom Latham's day! Short of a length, on off, extra bounce there. It takes the shoulder of Tom Latham's blade and balloons up just across the leg stumps. The keeper and the bowler runs forward to take it but the ball lands safe.
The ball is coming nicely to the batters. Length and on off. Latham keeps it out.
Fuller now, on off. Defended out.
Length ball, on off. Latham pushes it to mid on.

FOUR! Good timing from Devon Conway to get off the mark! This is full and outside off. Conway drives it gently through covers and it races away to the fence. That brings up 150 for New Zealand as well.
Outside off, Left alone.
Quick single! A loopy ball, outside off, driven to covers for a single. There was a shy at the bowler's end but the back up was positioned well.
Now comes down the track and keeps this flatter ball out.
Full again, slider this time, Latham watchfully blocks it.
Full and outside off. Blocked out.
Devon Conway walks out at number 3.

OUT! TAKEN! Finally, Bangladesh get the wicket. They needed this wicket really bad. This is full and outside off, asking Young to go for the drive. He nailed it in the previous delivery but this time ends up slicing it to point where Mohammad Naim takes it low and nicely. Bangladesh will look to build on this now. Will Young will be disappointed as he failed to convert this into a big one.

133 clicks, On a length, outside off. Left alone.

Fuller again, slower and outside off. Latham paddles it to square leg for a single.

Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.

Tossed up, on off. Defended out on the front foot.

Another solid defense from Young.
Touch fuller, straight on off, Defended out.
Length, on off. Blocked out.

Fuller and on off, pushed to mid on.
Drop and run! Length and on middle, nudged to mid-wicket for a quick single.
