Length ball, around off, jags back in as well, this is tucked to square leg for one.
On the pads, this is flicked to square leg.
Good seam position from Taskin, makes it to come back in, tight leave as well. Outside off. Young shoulders arms. The keeper dives to his left to take it.
Outside off again. Young lets it through.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
An appeal for LBW but there was a thick inside edge! A length ball, on off. Young looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
FOUR! Boundary off the blade now! Full and on middle. Latham pushes it gently wide of mid on for a boundary. Good start for New Zealand after the Lunch break.
On middle. Defended back to the bowler. Hossain shows his frustration as he has a go at the striker's stump.
A full toss, on off. Latham pushes it to cover.

Disappointment for Hossain! 5 runs now! Length and on middle. Young tucks it to short mid-wicket and runs across for a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses and overthrow means the Kiwis pick up a boundary.
Length ball, angling outside off. Young shoulders arms.
Touch fuller, on off. Defended.
Outside off, Left alone.
FOUR! EDGED! Latham playing with luck! Length ball, angling across, outside off. Latham looks to block it but gets an outside edge through gully for a boundary.
Lovely delivery! Taskin Ahmed has to stick to this length and ask questions to Latham! A length ball, outside off, extra bounce as well. Latham looks to defend but misses.
On middle, this is tucked away to mid-wicket.
On a length, on middle. Blocked out.
FOUR! Beautiful stroke! Full and outside off, this is driven through covers for a boundary.
Taskin Ahmed to bowl from the other end.

DROPPED! 7 runs altogether! Sloppy start from Bangladesh! A length ball, outside off, it lands and nips away. Young has a poke and gets an outside edge to first slip. The second slip fielder dives to his left and goes for it but fumbles and drops. It would have been wise if he had left for the first slip fielder to take it. The ball rolls to fine leg and till then the batters take three runs. There is a throw at the bowler's end but no back up means the ball races away to the fence. Hossain himself goes for it but in vain. Eventful start already.
Good bowling! Length ball, this one straightens up off the deck. Young had a look at it and withdraws his bat very late.
Outside off, on a length. Young shoulders arms to it.
Again this is outside off. Young offers no shot.
Length ball, outside off. Young leaves it alone.
Hossain starts with a full ball, way outside off. Young punches it to covers.
We are back for the post Lunch session. Both the openers walk out for the resumption. Ebadot Hossain to start with the ball.
... Day 1, Session 2 ...

The Kiwi openers on the other hand, were solid. There were a couple of nervous moments for Latham who was given out twice but the decisions were reversed but overall, the two have batted brilliantly. Latham especially who has managed to score quickly. Both are set now and will be eying big scores. Can they continue the dominance after the break? We will find out. Do join us at 6:10 am IST (12:40 am GMT).

To be honest, Bangladesh just weren’t at their best with the ball. They were way too wide outside off and did not make the most of the new ball. Whenever they hit the right areas, they did manage to cause problems but they weren’t consistent enough. Also, they were a tad unlucky too but overall, Haque will be disappointed with the effort of the bowlers.

End of an excellent session for the hosts and Latham will be thinking, it wasn’t that bad a toss to lose. Haque on the other hand, maybe regretting his decision to bowl first already. The visitors have a lot of thinking to do in the break.
A length ball, on off. Latham solidly blocks it. That will be Lunch on Day 1.
FOUR! Crunched! Captain leading from the front! A short of a length, on middle. Latham pulls it in front of square leg for a boundary.
Short and around off. Latham sways away from the line.
On the pads, this is tucked to square leg.
Good shot from Latham! Too full, on off, this is driven to mid off.
Length and on off. Blocked out.
BEATEN! 138 clicks! Good channel from Ahmed! On a length, just outside off. Young prods to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
A fuller-length ball, outside off. Latham looks to drive but gets an inside edge to fine leg and a single is taken. Was early to his shot.
On middle, on a length. Latham solidly defends it.
Full and on middle, this is pushed wide of mid on for a quick single.
Again this is outside off but Young leaves it alone this time.
FOUR! Placement! A length ball, way outside off. Young frees his arms and cuts it through point for a boundary.
Short of a length, on middle. Latham stays back and blocks it out.
Strays it on the pads, this is flicked to deep square leg for a couple.
On a length, on off. Defended.
Bangladesh are appealing for everything now! A length ball, this one just shapes away off the deck, just around off. Latham gets beaten as he looks to defend. An appeal but nothing given.
FOUR! Timed it really well! Pitches it up, outside off. Latham drives it through covers for a boundary.
Length ball, outside off. Latham covers his off stump and lets it through.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Another appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested! Height was the issue! Short of a length, on off. Young looks to defend but gets hit on the pads, there was extra bounce as well.
On the pads, this is flicked to square leg for a single.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Review time! Actually Bangladesh ran out of time and the review is not taken.

A length ball, this one comes back in, around middle and off. Latham looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal for LBW but not given. Bangladesh take the review but they ran out of time and the review is not taken.
FOUR! Another boundary! Short of a length, outside off. Latham looks to defend but this goes more off the other half through gully for a boundary.
Outside off, not played at.

DROP AND RUN! Fifty for Latham! The skipper leads from the front in a must-win game. A very good innings so far. Really played the good balls well and has cashed in on the poor deliveries. On a length and on off, Latham pushes it towards cover for one. Soaks in the applause from the crowd here. Needs to make it a big one now.
BEATEN! This one comes in with the angle, lands on off and straightens. Latham is beaten as he tries to defend.
Solid! Shohidul Islam attacks the stumps and on middle, defended.
FOUR! Latham moves onto 49 now! Shorter and outside off, Latham stands tall and pushes it through covers. Boundary.
On the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
Good length and on off, defended.
Another leave as this is again outside off. Also, a first warning for Taskin as he was stepping on the danger area in his followthrough.
Outside off, not played at.
Outside off, left alone.
Not sure why there was an appeal there! On a length and on off, Latham defends it on the pitch.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Fuller and on off, Latham leans into it and strokes it through covers. This one races away to the fence.
Well played in the end! Length and around off, this one holds its line. Young initially looks to defend but then pulls his bat back seeing the movement.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, defended.

Going over! Ebadot Hossain has been a little short than he needs to bowl on this surface. Again it is behind a length and on middle, Young looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal but turned down.
Angled into the middle pole, this is defended.
On middle, Young works it to mid-wicket.

Close! Once again luck not on the side of the visitors! Length and outside off, Young pushes at it away from the body, he gets an inside edge, it goes just past the off pole and down to fine leg for one.
Yet again outside off, Young does not fiddle with it.
Good length and on off, this one comes back in. Young plays it late and towards gully.
Drop and run! On off, this is pushed to cover for one.
Outside off, Young plays it past point and takes one.
Just outside off, an easy leave for Young.
Back of a length and on off, Latham stands tall and defends.
Another one which is outside off, not played at.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR RUNNING RUNS! Latham is scoring quickly. He moves onto 40. Short and on middle, this is pulled through mid-wicket. The mid on fielder chases it and flicks it back in but four has been ran.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
FOUR! Yet another edgy boundary! This is angled in from around the wicket, it lands and moves away. Latham pushes at it, it goes off the outside edge past gully and into the third man fence.
Another harmless nut outside off, easy leave.
On middle, angling in, defended nicely.
A little too short again, this one comes in with the angle. Young does well to get his hands out of the way and to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
Just outside off, Young does well to sway out of the way.
A sharp short ball, Young lets it go to the keeper.
Shortish and on off, Latham strokes it to point.
Fuller and on off, Latham pushes it to mid off.
Full and outside off, Latham looks to drive, hits the ground in the attempt and misses the ball. It is taken by the keeper. Half an appeal but nothing.

FOUR! Up and over! Luck so far has been on the side of New Zealand! Short and wide outside off, Latham slashes at it, it goes off the top edge and over the first slip fielder for a boundary. Fifty up for the Kiwis and it is a solid start for them.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, Latham pushes it to covers. The fielder misfields but no run taken.
Two more! Length and on off, Young pushes it through covers. Two taken.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off, comes back in but not enought o make the batter play.
On off, blocked.

Going down leg! Angled into the pads, Young looks to flick but misses. It hits the thigh pad and then almost deflects onto the stumps. The bowler is appeal but turned down. It goes past the leg pole by a whisker.

A huge appeal from the keeper but he is the only one doing so! A good delivery by Taskin. Goes full and this one swings in back late from off. Latham gets his front foot out in time and then works it through mid-wicket for one. The keeper thought it was pad.
On middle, Latham works it wide of mid on for one.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Crisp! What a shot! Second boundary in the over. Ebadot Hossain serves another half volley, this is driven through covers and it races away to the fence.
Around off, Latham plays it late and towards gully, the fielder dives to his left and stops one.
Good length and on off, defended.
FOUR! He did not even think of running there. Beautiful! Fuller and on off, Latham shows the full face of the bat and times it past mid off for a boundary.

DRINKS! A good hour of play for the Kiwis! Their openers have began well and now will want to capitalse on the hard work done by them so far. The wicket seems a really good one and it is now about cashing in for the Kiwi batters. Bangladesh need to bowl a lot more on the stumps, Ebadot Hossain, in the two overs he has bowled has been really good and the others too have to bowl similar lines and lengths to what he has done. Can they make the second part of the first session theirs?
Outside off, not played at.
Goes short, probably the first bumper, ducked under.
Slightly fuller this time, this is pushed to mid off.
Angled in on middle, Young plays it to mid on.
On the middle pole, Young keeps it out.
Outside off, Young does not fiddle with it.
A single to end! On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket for one.
On the stumps, Young keeps it out.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, defended.
Ebadot Hossain has been brilliant in the 8 balls he has bowled so far! Length and on off now, this lands and moves away. Young looks to defend but is beaten.
FOUR! A full toss and it is put away! Ebadot Hossain goes for the yorker but ends up serving a full toss, this is clipped nicely through mid-wicket, boundary.
On middle, Latham keeps it out.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed to covers.
That is a beauty! Length and on off, this lands and then moves away. Latham plays the original trajectory but gets beaten.
On middle, Latham pushes it to mid on.
On the pads, Young works it through square leg and takes one.
That is a very good leave! Just outside off, Young lets it be.
Outside off, Latham leaves it alone. End of an action-packed over.

NOT OUT! Going over! Latham, in the space of 4 balls has been given out twice but has been saved by the reviews. Bangladesh felt this one was dead but the extra bounce on this wicket saves Latham. On off, shorter, this one jags back in. Latham goes back and looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pads. Another appeal and the finger is raised again. Young walks up to his partner and after a chat, Latham reviews. Hawk Eye shows it to be going over.
Latham has been given out again! He reviews again. This looks a lot closer. Maybe high? We will have to wait and see.
Fuller and outside off, Latham leaves it alone.
Shot! Fuller and outside off, Latham leans into it and drives it through covers for two.
Has Ebadot Hossain done the trick again? Latham has been given out LBW but he reviews. Could be a good review.

NOT OUT! That is indeed missing leg! Did seem like it would, Latham knew it and hence, he reviewed immediately. This is angled into the pads, Latham looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. A huge shout and the finger is raised. Latham reviews and Hawk Eye shows it is going down leg. Ebadot Hossain bowled it from quite wide of the crease and it always seemed like going down leg.
FOUR! Flayed away! Welcome into the attack, Ebadot Hossain! Short and wide outside off, this is cut through point for a boundary.
This time gets the bag! A really good shot. Shorter and on off, Latham stands tall and pushes it through covers. Big boundaries so they get three.
On off, Latham plays it to covers.
On the stumps, Latham defends.
Solid! On a length and on off, Latham blocks.

Ambitious appeal but turned down! Really good delivery. The Bangladesh bowlers are getting into their own now. Length and on off, this lands and straightens. Latham looks to work it on the leg side. He misses to get hit high on the pads.
The stump at the non-striker's end plays as the 12th fielder! Saves a certain boundary! Fuller and on middle, this is driven straight but it hits the stumps at the other end.
Three good deliveries to end! On a length again and on off, Young lets the ball come to him and then plays it onto the ground.
Taskin is a quick learner. Hits the length again and on off, Young plays it nice and late and onto the ground.

EDGY FOUR! If there is a line and length you need to bowl on this wicket, then that is it. Straightaway causes problems but luck favors Young. This is slightly fuller and on off, it lands and holds its line. Young looks to defend, it goes off the outside edge, along the ground, past gully and down to the third man fence.
And again, outside off, not played at. The new ball is being wasted.
Taskin continues to keep the ball outside off, Young continues to leave it.
Angled into the pads, Young works it to mid-wicket.
A dot to end! A harmless nut outside off, Latham lets it go to the keeper.
Good length again and on off, Latham plays it to covers.
This one is on the pads, Latham works it but to square leg.
BEATEN! First delivery that has caused trouble to the batter! Length and on off, this lands and moves away. Latham is beaten as he tries to block.
Gets this one to shape away nicely but from outside off, left alone.
A lot of 'ohhs and ahhs' but that is a very good leave again! Just outside off, Latham covers his off pole and shoulders arms to it.
Two more! Fuller and on the pads, this is clipped through mid-wicket for two.
Yet another harmless ball, length and outside off, Young shoulders arms to this one.
Angled into the pads, Young misses out, he looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On middle, Young defends this time. Better, make the batter play a lot more.
And again, yet another leave! This time it is a good one by the batter! This one jags back in from outside off. Young watches it closely and lets it be.
Yet another leave! Need to make the batters play here. Outside off, left alone.
Outside off, left alone.
On off and on a length, Latham pushes it to covers.
Just outside off then, Latham shoulders arms to it.
Bends his back and bangs it short, extra bounce. Latham defends.
Solid! On off, Latham defends it on the off side.
Just outside off, Latham covers his off pole and leaves it alone.
Drags his length back this time and bowls it just outside off, left alone. Better over from Taskin.
Really good fielding! Fuller and on off, Young drives towards mid off. Mominul Haque there dives to his right and saves at least two.
Well bowled again! Fuller in length but slightly outside off, left alone.
This is the length you need to bowl on this wicket, ahead of a length and just behind the driving length. The line is also good, on off. Blocked.

Left on length! Taskin bowls this slightly shorter, just behind a length actually, this one jags back in. Young leaves it on length and it goes over the off pole. You can leave the ball on length here due to the extra bounce.
Really good! Length and on off, Young plays it right under his eyes and on the off side.
Gets this one to hold its line after landing it on off, Latham defends it on the off side. Bangladesh have not started that well here, the first two overs have not been that great.
Good leave there! Shoriful Islam gets it fuller this time and just outside off, Latham leaves it alone to the keeper.
FOUR! Up and over! Latham gets his second boundary! This is a gift! Short and wide outside off, it is cut over point for a boundary.
On the pads, Young now works it through square leg and gets to the other end.
Solid! Good length and on off, no movement for the left-hander. Blocked nicely.
Two! Good delivery though to begin with. This one lands on middle and holds its line. Young looks to defend, it goes off the inner half through square leg for a couple.
Who will bowl from the other end then? Shoriful Islam, the left armer will share the new ball.

FOUR! First boundary of the game and it comes on the 6th ball of the first over! A good start for the Kiwis. This is on the pads, Latham works it down to the fine leg fence. Judging by the first over, Bangladesh's decision to bowl first could prove costly. Seems a good wicket.
Young now is underway! On the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
Good carry there! Better from Taskin. A lot closer this time to the off pole, still not enough to make the batter play. He gets it to bounce and zip through nicely.
Latham and the Kiwis are underway! Shorter and on off, Latham pushes it towards cover and gets to the other end.
And again, keeps it outside off, Latham does not fiddle with it. No movement on the first two deliveries.
Starts off with a full one, looking for some swing but there ain't any. Left alone as it is outside off.

We are moments away from the first ball now! First though it is time for the National Anthems! First it is Bangladesh's turn and then the Kiwis. We are done with the Anthems and now the Bangladesh players make their way out to the middle. They are followed by the two, New Zealand openers, Tom Latham and Will Young. Taskin Ahmed has the new ball in hand. Here we go... HOLD ON! Bangladesh have some issue with the ball, maybe it is not the ball they had picked. Out comes the box, the right one has been picked now and we are ready to go.
So both sides make changes! Daryl Mitchell come in for Rachin Ravindra! Bangladesh on the other hand, make two as they get in Naim and Hasan for Joy and Rahim.

BANGLADESH (PLAYING XI) - Shadman Islam, Mohammad Naim (IN FOR Mushfiqur Rahim), Najmul Hossain Shanto, Mominul Haque (C), Nurul Hasan, Liton Das (WK), Yasir Ali, Mehidy Hasan, Taskin Ahmed, Ebadot Hossain, Shoriful Islam.
New Zealand (Playing XI) - Tom Latham (C), Will Young, Devon Conway, Ross Taylor, Henry Nicholls, Daryl Mitchell, Tom Blundell (WK), Kyle Jamieson, Tim Southee, Neil Wagner, Trent Boult
TOSS - Bangladesh have won the toss and have OPTED TO FIELD!

The Kiwis, well, despite the loss are overwhelming favourites. Also, this is Ross Taylor’s last game in this format for them so they would love to give him a fitting end. The last game was surely a wake up call for them and knowing this New Zealand side, they will be wanting to hit back hard. They need a win and nothing else will do. Will they level the series? We will find out. Welcome to the coverage of Day 1 of the second Test.

If you ever thought Bangladesh would go lead the series at the start of the second Test, you should be buying yourself a lottery ticket. What a win and what a performance that was in the first game. The odds were heavily stacked against them but they ended up doing what they never managed to do before. BEAT THE KIWIS IN THEIR OWN BACKYARD! Now though they can look at the bigger picture and that is win a Test series here. A feat which many teams have struggled to do in recent times but Bangladesh have a chance, they just need to avoid a loss, a lot easier to be said than done. They have the momentum though and will be rearing in confidence. Can they upset the odds twice in a row?
... Day1, Session 1 ...

Time for the action to begin! The New Zealand players make their way out to the middle. So do the Bangladesh openers - Shadman Islam and Mohammad Naim. Tim Southee has the new ball in hand. Here we go...

Bangladesh will now have to score 395 to avoid an innings defeat! That is an uphil task for a team which failed to score even half of that in their first innings. Will they put up a better fight this time around or will they once again surrender to the New Zealand bowling attack?

So, the news coming in is that, New Zealand HAVE ENFORCED THE FOLLOW-ON! Quite obvious, they have a massive lead and it really made no sense for them to bat again. Yes, many would have said, maybe they could have given Rosco yet another go with the bat but pretty sure the Kiwi legend himself would have wanted his side to enforce it.

Welcome everyone for the third day of this Test match. Usually, we call it the 'moving day' but this game has already moved in the direction of New Zealand to a point of no return. The home team has dominated this Test from the word go - first with the bat and then with the ball. They have gained a hefty 395-run lead and in all likelihood, Bangladesh will be asked to bat again. Stay tuned, we will keep you informed...
... DAY 3, SESSION 1 ...

Bangladesh are well behind in this game! They will need a miracle if they are to get back in this game. Really do not see that happening though. All they can hope to do is show some fight with either the bat or the ball, whatever they will be asked to do. What I mean by that is, it will be interesting to see if New Zealand enforce the follow-on or will we have the opportunity to see Ross Taylor bat once more in whites? All of those questions will be answered on Day 3. Do join us for the action which begins at 0330 am IST (2200 pm GMT, previous day) our build-up though begins earlier. Till then, take care and goodbye!

The man of the moment, Trent Boult is up for a chat. He says that it is a special moment to pick 300 Test wickets and there are some big names on the list as well but it feels good to be on it. Adds that the conditions were good, there was swing as well and they made the most of it. Tells that they are bowling well and are looking forward to Day 3.

It is Trent Boult who leads his team off! Rightly so, he was exceptional on Day 2! Completed 300 Test wickets and ended with a fifer to round off what was a complete day for the Kiwis! They just could not have asked for a better day of Test cricket. First it was Latham, Conway and Blundell who helped them go past the 500-run mark. After declaring, the Kiwi bowlers were on song, Boult and Southee made quick work of the top order. There was some resistance showed from Yasir and Nurul Hasan as the two added 60 but once that partnership was broken, the lower order did not contribute a lot.

OUT! TIMBER! Five-fer for Trent Boult! 301 and counting...! A length ball, around off, was the slower ball. Islam looks to push at it but misses and the ball clips the top of off pole. That will be Stumps on Day 2.
Commentary.Howout: b Trent Boult

Commentary.Commentary: Full ball, outside off. Islam looks to heave it but misses.
BEATEN! A full ball, outside off. Ebadot Hossain looks to drive but gets beaten. Lovely stuff from Kyle Jamieson.
A pacy short ball, outside off. Left alone.
Ebadot Hossain is the last man in.

OUT! TAKEN! Now the set batter, Yasir Ali departs! A short ball, on middle. Yasir Ali pulls it, not quite of the middle as it goes off the toe end of the bat towards deep mid-wicket. Daryl Mitchell there, dives low and forward to take it. Very good catch and also end of a fine knock as well.
Commentary.Howout: c Daryl Mitchell b Kyle Jamieson

Commentary.Commentary: The physio is out to have a look! The magic spray does its job and Yasir is fine to continue.
On a length, on middle, tucked away to square leg. It came off the gloves and Yasir Ali looks in a bit of pain here.
Short ball, angling across, just around off. Ali looks to ramp it away but misses.
On middle. Blocked out.

FIVE RUNS! Overthrows! A short ball, on off. Yasir hops and looks to defend and does it uppishly towards point. They take a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. No back up and it races away to the fence.
Bangs a short ball, down leg. Yasir misses his pull.
Back of a length, on off. Blocked out.
Full and on middle. Gets an inside edge onto the pads.
JAFFA! Absolute beauty! A length ball, around off, swinging in, Ali gets beaten on the inside edge but the ball bounces just in front of the off  pole and that saves him.
Boult comes over the wicket and serves a full ball, angling on the pads. Ali misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.A mild appeal for LBW follows.
A full ball, on off, this is driven through covers for a couple of runs.
Maiden fifty for Yasir Ali! He is sticking at one end! A short ball, on middle. Ali miscues it completely and it drops on the leg side. A quick single taken.
Shoriful Islam walks out to bat!

OUT! TAKEN! Bangladesh are falling apart. A length ball, around off. Taskin Ahmed swings hard across but gets a leading edge towards mid-wicket where Will Young takes a skier. Finally, someone not named Boult or Southee gets a wicket.
Commentary.Howout: c Will Young b Kyle Jamieson

Commentary.Commentary: On middle, pulled away to deep mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Edged! Short on middle. Ali looks to pull but gets a top edge over the slip cordon and towards the third man fence.
On middle, pushed through mid-wicket for a couple of runs as there was a midfield as well.
Around off. Ahmed swings across and gets a leading edge. It drops n front of the running mid off fielder. He picks up and there was a direct hit at the bowler's end but the batter was in. Two.
A run out appeal and it is taken upstairs! The batter seems in.
Short in length, around off. Ahmed looks to block it but misses. That whizzed past the outside edge.
Taskin Ahmed walks out to bat!

OUT! TIMBER! 300 Test wickets for Trent Boult! Acknowledgment and appreciation from his teammates and the spectators as well. A delivery which deserved a wicket as well. A length ball, around off, angling it in. Mehidy Hasan was struggling against Boult and this time he fades away. This one comes back in and beats the outside edge as Hasan looks to defend. The off stump gets disturbed.
Commentary.Howout: b Trent Boult

Commentary.Commentary: Length and on off. Blocked out.
A sharp bouncer now, on middle. Hasan sits under it.
Boult sticking with short balls, Hasan looks to defend but misses.
A full ball, swinging back in sharply, on middle. Ali gets his bat down in time and manages an inside edge onto his pads.
Almost a yorker, on off. Yasir does well to dig it out.
Way outside off. Left alone.
Another solid block from Ali.
Full ball, outside off. Defended out.
This one swings away late, full and outside off. Ali shoulders arms.
Length ball, outside off, angling away. Hasan has a poke and misses.
Full on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Short again, Hasan drops his wrists and lets it through.
129 clicks! Short ball, angling on off. Hasan sways away from the line.
On a length, outside off. Hasan hops and blocks it.
Full ball, on off. Yasir shuffles across and flicks it through mid-wicket. Neil Wagner gives a long chase and saves a single.
Superb over from Southee! Right on the money! Fuller ball, outside off. Hasan has a poke at it but misses.
Angles a fuller ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Short and down the leg side. Left alone.
BEATEN! Lovely stuff! On a length, just around off. Hasan looks to defend but misses.
Fuller this time, Defended out.
BEATEN! This is a beauty! Short of a length, just around off, makes Hasan play it. He tries to block it but gets beaten on the outside edge
Around off. Blocked out.
Good fielding! A full ball, way outside off. Hasan drives it through covers. A long chase for the fielder and he does well to flick it back near the ropes.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Another leave by Mehidy Hasan. This is fuller and outside off.
Much closer to the off pole. Hasan leaves it alone again.
Length ball, steep bounce but was outside off. Easy leave.
Fuller and on middle, this is hit to mid-wicket.
Is that a drop? Looked like it came off the helmet! A short ball, on middle. Yasir Ali misses his pull and gets hit on the helmet. A mandatory concussion protocol follows...
On middle, on a length. Blocked out.
Length and on middle, tucked away to square leg for a single.
On middle. Hasan is too early as he looks to flick, gets a leading edge towards gully where the fielder does well to stop it.
Full ball, swinging away late, outside off. Left alone.
Shorter in length, on middle, Ali gets on top of the bounce and pulls it through mid-wicket. Two.
100 up for Bangladesh! Length ball, swinging, on middle, this is flicked to deep square leg for a single.

Full, outside off. Left alone.
Three now! Length and on off. Yasir punches it through covers and takes three before the fielder chases and cuts it off.
FOUR! Welcomes Boult with a boundary! A short ball, angling across, on off. Ali pulls it, not in any control and gets a top edge, high and to the fine leg fence.

Fuller, quickly and on off. Hasan gets his bat down in time to defend to gully.
Full, outside off, shaping away as well. Hasan lets it through.
On middle, this is flicked to square leg for a single.
Fuller now, on off, pushed to mid off.

Outside off. Left alone.
WIDE! Short and on middle. Hasan sits under it. A wide given for height.
Keeps serving in that region, around off. Hasan covers his stumps and lets it through.
Length and outside off. Hasan leaves it alone.
A length ball, angling outside off. Hasan tries to shoulders arms but the ball hits the toe end of the bat and bounces in front of the keeper.
BEATEN! On a length, outside off. Hasan looks to defend but misses.
Fuller and outside off, pushed to covers for a quick single.
Mehidy Hasan walks out!

OUT! LBW! New Zealand have broken the partnership and it is Southee who gives the breakthrough. It looked plumb of the naked eye. A length ball, around middle and leg, it lands and nips back in. Nurul Hasan looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal and up goes the finger. Hasan takes the review and the Ball Tracker shows umpire's call on wickets hitting.

On middle, this is punched to mid on.

DRINKS! Good work from Yasir Ali and Nurul Hasan as they have crossed the 50-run partnership. Both have done really well so far to steady the ship. Hasan is playing more quickly while Ali is playing the second fiddle.

FOUR! That is brilliantly played! Short and on the body, Hasan rolls his wrists over the ball, gets it in the gap in the square leg region and bags a boundary.
On off, this is pushed to covers.

On the pads, this is left alone.

Shorter and on off, this is pushed through covers for one.
Goes wide outside off, Hasan does not fiddle with it.
On middle, Ali flicks it through mid-wicket for one.
Good length and on off, Ali stays back and defends.
Shorter in length, Hasan pulls it nicely towards fine leg for one. Neil Wagner dives forward but it falls in front of him.

Outside off, left alone.
Shorter and outside off, left alone.
That is a beauty! Length and on off, this lands and then moves away. Yasir is beaten as he tries to block.

NO BALL! Angled into the pads, Ali works it through square leg for one. A no ball signaled as Wagner overstepped.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! That is a beautiful stroke! Fuller and shaping away. Hasan creams it through covers, this one races away to the fence.
On off, defended.
Fuller and on middle, this is played to mid on.
Outside off, left alone nicely.
BEATEN! That is loose! Shorter in length and outside off, Ali hangs his bat out and gets beaten.
A bumper, Yasir lets it go over him.
Good length and on off, Ali plays it back to the bowler.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
On the stumps, kept out well.
Another leave as this is not bowled on the stumps.

FOUR! Up and over! Short and wide outside off, Hasan plays it up and over the point fielder and into the fence behind.
Fuller and on off, Hasan plays it back to the bowler.
Good delivery! A yorker on the pads, Hasan gets his bat down in time and works it through square leg for two.
Fuller and on off, this is driven through covers for two.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! Edgy! Bangladesh won't mind how they come as long as they do! Length and on off, this one straightens. Yasir goes back to defend, it goes off the outside edge past gully and down to the third man fence.

Outside off, left alone.

Shorter and on off, Ali keeps it out.

Outside off, Ali shoulders arms to this one.

Now plays out the good ball! Length and on middle, blocked.

We are back for the final session and it is going to be a long one! 38 overs to go. Liton Das and Yasir Ali make their way out to the middle to continue their innings. Trent Boult to continue.
... Day 2, Session 3 ...

Yet another successful session for New Zealand! It felt like their bowlers were itching to come outside and make their presence felt. The deadly duo of Tim Southee and Trent Boult combined to take all the wickets and keep the visitors on the back foot. Other than the first over, it went all downhill for Bangladesh and now Ali and Das have already started the repair work. New Zealand declared on 521/6 and gave a small passage of play to the bowlers. Boult and Southee presented some beautiful action and will hope to continue it after the Tea break as well. Stay tuned as we will be back for the final session.
Length ball, angling on the pads. Ali misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. An appeal for LBW but not given, was sliding down. That will be Tea on Day 2.
Bangs a short ball, on middle. Ali sits under it.
Length ball, way outside off. Ali shoulders arms to it.
FOUR! Nicely driven! A full ball, swinging away, outside off. Ali drives it through covers for a boundary. Holds the pose as well.
Length and on off, Blocked out.

Length ball, outside off. Left alone.

On a length, on off. Blocked out.

Straight, on the pads, tucked to mid-wicket.

On middle, on a length. Blocked out.
A sharp outswinger! Length and outside off. Left alone.
Lovely bowling! Again this one swings touch away. On a length, on off. Ali defends it off the outer half.
Length and on off. Blocked out.
Yasir Ali walks out to the middle.

OUT! KNOCKED OUT! Through the gates! Bangladesh in all sorts of trouble here! The skipper goes for a duck! Southee hurls and serves it from over the wicket. On a length and swinging back in, on middle. Mominul Haque leaves a gap between the bat and pad as he tries to push and pays the price. The ball sneaks through and rattles the stumps.

Length, on off. Shanto blocks it out.
Now gets on top of the bounce and blocks it out.
On a length, on off. Shanto defends off the front foot.

Fuller ball, on off. Haque looks to defend but gets an outside edge to gully.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Mohammad Naim was facing the fire and walks back to the pavilion on a duck. A length ball, outside off, the extra bounce does the trick as the ball shoots off the deck. Mohammad Naim hops and tries to block it but it takes the inside edge and rattles the stumps. New Zealand on the front foot early on.

Three more! Positive start from Bangladesh! Length ball, outside off. Islam punches off the back foot through covers for three runs. The ball does not have legs to run away and the fielder cuts it off.

Bangladesh and Shadman Islam are underway! A full ball, swinging in, on middle. Islam punches it softly straight down the ground for a couple of runs.

That's all from this Test match. The series ends 1-1 and it's a great result as far as Bangladesh are concerned as they gained a lot of confidence and positives for future along with vital points for the ICC World Test Championship, 2021-23. Plenty of cricketing action is going on, do visit the fixtures page and enjoy our coverage. Cheers!

Mominul Haque, the captain of Bangladesh, says that they were really happy with the first Test but are disappointed here. Mentions that it was challenging for them to keep up the momentum. Feels that one needs to have a good mindset while playing overseas. Tells that they still have some positives despite losing this Test. Credits Liton Das for his knock and says that when he was batting, the pitch didn't look difficult to bat.

Devon Conway is adjudged the Player of the Series! Says that he is happy with how the series went. Mentions that he had to contribute day in and day out. Tells that one had to adjust to the game plans. Says that it was nice to build a partnership with Tom Latham. On Ross Taylor, he says that Rosco has played so many Test matches and has an enormous amount of knowledge of the game. Adds that Taylor is a great bloke to be around and they will miss him very much.

The Kiwi skipper, Tom Latham, is also the Player of the Match. Says that they entered this Test match 0-1 down and needed to correct a few mistakes. Feels that the partnerships in the first innings helped them. On being a part of history by taking the catch off Taylor's bowling, Latham smiles and replies that he never felt more pressure while taking a catch. States that they had the advantage of knowing the conditions better than anyone and they put up a perfect performance. Further says that New Zealand have played well on different kind of pitches in the recent past and also credits Bangladesh for the way they fought in this series. Signs off by saying that it won't be the same without Ross Taylor, in the team and in the slip cordon.

Ross Taylor is delighted to finish off his Test career with a win and with a wicket. Admits that Bangladesh put them under a lot pressure several times and feels that it's a fair result to this series. Praises the batting and bowling of his side and also appreciates the way they bounced back after the last defeat. With tongue in cheek, Rosco says that he was worried about coming back tomorrow (Day 4) and doing the warm-up drills. Mentions that he is proud to represent his country and tells that it's a great way to finish.

Farewell Rosco! This Test also marked the end of an era in New Zealand cricket as Ross Taylor played his last in whites. The icon of NZ cricket surpassed Stephen Fleming in his final Test match and joined Daniel Vettori to become the country's most-capped Test cricketer. If the renaissance of New Zealand cricket is credited to Brendon McCullum, one must remember Taylor's contribution, both as the leader and the star batter of the team. He played many great knocks in his 16-year old career but the standout one has to be his innings against Pakistan in the 2011 World Cup which earned him the tag of the Pallekele Plunderer. Rosco made it a habit of sticking his tongue out while celebrating a ton and we still remember how he stuck his tongue out twice after reaching his double ton in 2015 against Australia. Not just his batting, the Black Caps are going to miss those bucket-hands in the slip cordon as well. Luteru Ross Poutoa Lote Taylor signs off from Test cricket and he will put a full stop to his illustrious international career after the ODI series against Australia and Netherlands. Enjoy it while it lasts. Here he is having a quick word.

New Zealand would be relieved to level the series. It was a hurtful loss for them in the first Test where they got outplayed by a very clinical Bangla unit. That defeat came as a huge surprise but the Kiwis didn't take long to prove that it was just an aberration. Skipper Tom Latham led from the front with a masterful double century while Devon Conway continues to take giant strides. He stroked a delightful century to become the first player in the history of Test cricket to start the career with 5 fifty-plus scores in the first 5 games. Their knocks combined with some impactful pace bowling handed them a commanding 395-run lead and despite Bangladesh fighting hard on Day 3 after being asked to follow-on, the result was never in doubt. It turned out to be a special game for Trent Boult who joined Tim Southee, Daniel Vettori and Sir Richard Hadlee in an exclusive club of New Zealand cricketers to take 300 Test wickets. A special mention for Liton Das who showed a lot of courage and stroked a fantastic century, albeit in a losing cause.

One swallow doesn't make a summer, that phrase aptly describes the situation of Bangladesh. Without any shade of a doubt, the Bangla Tigers punched above their weight to upset the Kiwis in the first Test but after scaling the height of Mount Maunganui, Bangladesh fell in familiar abyss. They missed a golden chance of registering a Test series win on NZ soil by putting out an abysmal bowling and batting show. The touring team will be regretting at the moment but still, there will be a sense of pride in sharing the trophy on the foreign land, especially in Tests.

OUT! Goosebumps, Rosco has a fairytale end to his Test career, a fitting end, the crowd has gone bonkers. A tossed up delivery, outside off, Ebadot attempts to heave it over the leg side but only manages a top edge. Latham runs across a bit to his left and dives to complete the catch at mid-wicket. Ross celebrates with a big smile and is mobbed by his teammates. NEW ZEALAND WIN BY AN INNINGS AND 117 RUNS.
Commentary.Howout: c Tom Latham b Ross Taylor

Commentary.Commentary: Full again, on middle. Ebadot Hossain defends it out. The crowd is loving it.

Short of a length, on the body. Taskin Ahmed gets himself in an awkward position. He manages to fend it away to short leg.

Short ball, on middle. Taskin Ahmed ducks under it.

Short one on middle, Taskin Ahmed ducks under it.
Short of a length, on leg. Taskin Ahmed tucks it to short fine leg.

Full and on middle, Ebadot Hossain stays back and defends it out.

Ebadot Hossain is the last batsman to come in.

Fuller in length, on off. Taskin Ahmed drives it to mid off. A maiden for Neil Wagner.
Bangs a short one, on middle. Taskin Ahmed ducks under it.
Full and on middle, Taskin Ahmed knocks it to mid on.

Gets behind the line of the delivery and blocks.

Bouncer, Shoriful sways away with ease.

Around off, on a length, defended to the off side.

OUT! LBW! Liton Das' innings comes to an end. A wonderful innings though. Kyle Jamieson bowls a length ball, on middle and this one jags back in. Liton Das is caught at the crease and looks to work it on the leg side but misses. He gets hit on the pads. Kyle Jamieson appeals and the umpire straightaway raises his dreaded finger. Liton Das decides to challenge the umpire and opts for a review. UltraEdge shows there is a flat line as the ball passes the bat. Ball Tracker shows the ball is pitching outside off, the impact is in line and it is umpire's call on hitting in the wickets. So, Liton Das will have to depart after a terrific knock. His fighting knock is appreciated by the Bangladeshi camp. New Zealand just two wickets away now.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Kyle Jamieson

Commentary.Commentary: Bangladesh have taken a review for LBW. UltraEdge shows there is no bat involved. Ball Tracker shows that the ball is pitching outside off, the impact is in line and it is umpire's call on hitting the wickets. So, the original decision stands. Bangladesh retain their review.
That one kept a little low! Length ball, on off. Liton Das does well to bring his bat down in time. Few words exchanged by Kyle Jamieson there!
Fuller in length, on off. Taskin Ahmed pushes it to mid on.

CENTURY! Liton Das gets it. A touch short in length outside off, Liton Das cuts it to deep point and beats the diving fielder positioned in that region. He comes back for the second run. The crowd is up on its feet. Liton Das removes his helmet and raises his bat to acknowledge the applause. He has deserved this. This is his second Test hundred. Came to bat with his team in all sorts of trouble and has played a gem of a knock here. It seems that his knock won't matter much in deciding the result but at least he has shown the courage to fight.
