FOUR! Beautiful shot! Fuller in length, on off. Taskin Ahmed drives it through mid off. The fielder gives it a chase but the ball wins the race.
On middle, worked on the leg side for a single. Liton Das moves to 90!
FOUR! That is slapped! Short of a length, on leg. Liton Das comes dancing down the track and slaps it to wide long off for a boundary. Extraordinary shot that!
FOUR! Pulled away! Short of a length, on middle. Liton Das reads the length early and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Back of a length, on middle. Liton Das defends it out.
Liton Das has been hit on the thumb and the physios are out to have a look. They apply some magic spray and he seems fine now. We are good to resume again...
The artificial lights are switched on.
Short of a length, on middle. Liton Das stands up on his toes and defends it off the shoulder of his bat to the off side. Well, that came off the gloves actually.
Back of a length, outside off. Taskin Ahmed fends it away to the off side.
Taskin Ahmed is the new batsman in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Kyle Jamieson comes into the attack and gets a wicket straightaway. New Zealand inching closer to level the series now. The delivery is on the shorter side, on middle. Mehidy Hasan stays back and looks to defend with a dead bat but gets squared up due to the extra bounce. The ball goes off the outside edge and flies to the second slip fielder. Tom Latham has very good hands and he doesn't drop those. Five catches in the match for Latham and he becomes the first player in Test history to score 250-plus runs and take five catches. Mehidy Hasan is disappointed as he walks back to the pavilion. The Bangladesh tail has been exposed now.
Commentary.Howout: c Tom Latham b Kyle Jamieson

Commentary.Commentary: Good length, outside off. Mehidy Hasan is not interested in playing that. He shoulders arms.
On a length, outside off. Liton Das steers it to deep point for a single.
Fuller, on off. Driven to mid off.
Short of a length, outside off. Liton Das guides it to third man for a couple of runs.

Drinks break. It's been a good battle with Bangladesh fighting hard on the back of Liton's unbeaten knock. New Zealand are made to toil hard for wickets. They need another four wickets in the next hour or so to put this Test to bed today itself. Can they do it? The second new ball will be due in 9 overs.
Comes 'round the wicket and bowls a short-of-a-length ball, outside off. Mehidy Hasan drops his bat and lets it sail through.
On a length, on leg. Mehidy Hasan tucks it to short fine leg.
Short of a length, down leg. Mehidy Hasan offers no shot and lets it be.
Short and on middle and leg. Mehidy Hasan ducks under that one.
Back of a length, on leg. Liton Das tucks it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Short of a length, on off. Liton Das stands tall and drops it down with soft hands.
Length ball, well outside off. Mehidy Hasan looks to drive but misses. Daryl Mitchell falls in his followthrough and rolls down the pitch before getting up.
Well bowled! Good-length ball, around off, shaping away. Mehidy Hasan looks to defend. The ball whistles past the outside edge there.
On a length, on middle. Mehidy Hasan defends it on the leg side.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length, on middle. Liton Das tucks it to the leg side for a single.
Fuller in length, on off. Liton Das drives it to mid off.
Back of a length, on off. Mehidy Hasan defends it to the off side.
Back of a length, on middle. Mehidy Hasan blocks it out from the crease.
Neil Wagner switches to 'round the wicket, bowls a short one, on off. Mehidy Hasan stands up on his toes and defends it out.
Short of a length, outside off. Mehidy Hasan sways away from that one.
Back of a length, outside off. Mehidy Hasan evades the line and lets it be.
Short and on middle, Mehidy Hasan ducks underneath.
Good shot! Straight from Daryl Mitchell, on leg. Liton Das flicks it through mid-wicket and grabs a couple.
On a good length, on off. Liton Das blocks it out to the off side.
On middle, nudged to deep square leg for a single.
On a length, outside off. Mehidy Hasan shoulders arms.
Length ball, outside off. Liton Das cuts it towards point. Tom Latham does well there to half stop the ball. A single is taken.
On a good length, outside off. Liton Das dabs it to gully.
It has turned a bit gloomy out there but there is no immediate threat of any rain. The floodlights can be switched on, if needed.
Short to finish the over! Bangs a short one, on middle. Mehidy Hasan ducks under this one.
Wagner goes full this time, on off. Mehidy Hasan drives it towards covers.
Back of a length, on middle. Mehidy Hasan does well to sway away from the line. He lets this one through.
Neil Wagner is continuing with his short stuff. Short again on leg, Mehidy Hasan sits under this one.
Short and leg-lined. Mehidy Hasan ducks under it.
Short and outside off, angling further away. Mehidy Hasan leaves it alone.
On a length, on off. Liton Das is solid in his defense.
On a length, outside off. Liton Das presses forward and blocks it out.
On a length, on off. Liton Das defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Excellent timing! Short of a length, on middle. Liton Das pulls it with disdain to deep square leg and bags a boundary. He will be eyeing a ton here.
On middle, defended on the leg side.
On off, kept out.
Fullish, on off. Mehidy Hasan works it to mid on.
Touch fuller, outside off. Mehidy Hasan reaches out for it and drives it over point for a couple of runs.
On a length, outside off. Mehidy Hasan lets it be.
Full and wide, outside off. Mehidy Hasan shoulders arms.
Short of a length, outside off. Mehidy Hasan defends it out.
Back of a length, on off. Mehidy Hasan drops his hands and sways away from the line.

OUT! CAUGHT! What a catch by Neil Wagner! Daryl Mitchell gets the much-needed breakthrough and breaks this century partnership. Good-length ball, on off. Nurul Hasan looks to drive this on the up but doesn't get his timing right. The ball is sliced towards wide mid off. Neil Wagner runs to his left and dives and holds onto that one. Daryl Mitchell is all pumped up and New Zealand have got the opening now. Mehidy Hasan walks in next to bat.
Commentary.Howout: c Neil Wagner b Daryl Mitchell

Commentary.Commentary: On middle, Nurul Hasan nudges it to mid-wicket.
On a length, on off. Nurul Hasan presses forward and blocks it out.
Fuller, on middle. Nurul Hasan drives it straight back and knocks the stumps at the other end.
Touch fuller, on middle. Nurul Hasan stays solid in his defense.
On a length, on middle. Nurul Hasan is solid in his defense.
Back of a length, on leg. Nurul Hasan pulls it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Good-length ball, outside off. Nurul Hasan looks to defend but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.

FOUR! Slightly overpitched outside off, Nurul Hasan leans into it and drives it uppishly through covers. Neil Wagner gives it a good chase but the ball wins the race. A boundary to bring up the century stand.
Back of a length, on the body. Liton Das fends it away to fine leg for a single.
Good-length ball, on off. Liton Das drives it to mid off.

In the air, but safe! Short and on middle. Nurul Hasan mistimes his pull behind square leg. Devon Conway runs across to his right from the deep to catch it but the ball falls well short of him. A single taken.
On a good length, on middle. Liton Das defends it from the crease.
On a good length, outside off. Liton Das shoulders arms.
Length ball, on off. Liton Das blocks it out.
FOUR! Liton Das is dealing in boundaries now, his 10th of this innings. Length ball, outside off. Liton Das steers it through gully for a boundary.
Short ball, on middle. Nurul Hasan mistimes his pull over mid-wicket. Shouts of catch but the ball falls in no man's land. A single is taken.
Good-length ball, outside off. Nurul Hasan drives it towards covers.
Bangs a short one, on middle. Liton Das ducks underneath. Another expensive over from this end.
FOUR! He's showing his class now. Overpitched delivery, on off. Liton Das caresses it back past the bowler for a boundary straight down the ground.
Back of a length, on off. Liton Das keeps it out.
FOUR! Hat-trick of boundaries! Width on offer, outside off. Liton Das opens the face of the bat and drives it through covers for another boundary. Exquisite shot!
FOUR! Shot! Touch fuller on off, Liton Das drives it through mid off for a boundary. Pure timing.

FOUR! Edged but safe! Length ball, outside off. Liton Das looks to drive. The ball goes off the outside edge and races away to third man for a boundary. That also brings up the fifty for Liton Das. He receives applause from his teammates.
On off, shortish, it is pushed to covers.
FOUR! This is pulled, short and on middle, it is hammered through mid-wicket for a boundary. 200 up!
This one stays very low! First real sign of uneven bounce! Length and on off, this one stays very low. Hasan looks to defend and it hits the toe-end of his blade.
Around middle, defended soundly by Nurul.
On middle, kept out again.
Good length and on off, defended.
FOUR! Short and on the body, Das pulls, it goes through mid-wicket for yet another boundary. A huge over for Bangladesh comes to an end, 17 from it.
Hasan now takes one as he helps this shortish delivery down to fine leg.
Short and on the body, Das pulls it through square leg for one.
SIX! That has gone over the fence! Das into the 40s. So clever there! This is short and just outside off, Das upper cuts it over the slip cordon and it goes all the way.
FOUR! Short and pulled away! He finds the gap in the square leg region and bags a boundary.
This though was a length ball, defended.
WIDE! Way too short, it goes over the batter's head. Wided. There are five fielders on the leg side so it is Kyle Jamieson's turn to bang a few short.
Goes wide of the crease and bowls it full and on middle, Hasan works it to mid on.
On middle, defended.

FOUR! Into the fence! Short and on the body, Hasan pulls it down towards fine leg. This one races away to the fence. Kyle Jamieson ran the wrong way there. He started to run to his left and then realized that the ball has sped through to his right. Southee is not impressed. The 50-run stand comes up!
Goes short again and on middle, Das pulls it through square leg for one.
Uppish but safe! Fuller and outside off, Das looks to drive but this goes off the outer half through point for two.
And again, a controlled pull shot through square leg to a short ball but just for a single.
A short ball, Hasan pulls it through square leg for one, nice controlled pull shot.
Good shot! On off, this is hit on the up to the man at covers.
On middle, Hasan defends.
FOUR! That is a hit-me ball! Short and wide outside off, this is slapped through point for a boundary.
Good length and on middle, defended.
Three! Angled into middle, this is worked through mid-wicket. Three taken.
Fuller and on middle, Hasan pushes it to mid on.
On middle, Hasan defends it onto the ground.
Short and this is pulled away nicely through square leg for one.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
Angled into the pads, Das works it through square leg for two.
Angled into middle, defended.
The physio is out now to have a look at struggling Nurul. The repair work has been done.
Back of a length and on middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Nicely played but Hasan limps as he runs to the other end. Shorter and outside off, this is guided through point for a boundary.
On off, Nurul guides it to point.
Angled into middle, Das gets the bat down in time and works it through square leg for one.
Fuller and on middle, Das drives but to mid off.
Good length and on off, blocked.
Kyle Jamieson to bowl from the other end.
Length ball, coming back in, on middle. Nurul Hasan pushes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Shot! Short of a length, on middle. Nurul Hasan pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fuller again, on middle. Nurul Hasan defends it back to the bowler. Tim Southee has a shy at the striker's end but misses. Nurul Hasan was inside the crease though.
Goes full, on middle. Nurul Hasan watchfully digs it out.
Length ball, on middle, nipping in. Nurul Hasan defends it on the leg side.
Good-length ball, on middle. Nurul Hasan blocks it out.
We are back for the final session! The players stride out to the middle. Liton Das and Nurul Hasan jog out to resume their innings as well. Tim Southee to begin proceedings...
... DAY 3, SESSION 3 ...

A delightful afternoon session for New Zealand after a sedate start to the day's play for them. Three wickets in the second session and the hosts have inched closer to a series-levelling victory. Neil Wagner bowled with a lot of fire while the rest of the bowlers rallied around him. Bangladesh fought for a little while and tried to stay positive but things unravelled rather too quickly for them. Liton Das and Nurul Hasan are the last recognised batsmen left and the touring team would be wishing for a big partnership between them. Do Bangladesh have it in them to drag this Test match into Day 4? Join us at 8.30 am IST (3 am GMT) to find out.
Fuller in length this time, on off. Liton Das drives it to the man at mid off. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 3!
FOUR! Quality shot! Short again, on middle. Liton Das this time pulls it through square leg for another boundary. Hands on the head for Neil Wagner.
FOUR! Great shot! Short ball, on middle. Liton Das watches the ball closely and pulls it behind square on the leg side for a boundary.
Well bowled! Short of a length, on middle. Liton Das sways away from the line and lets it through.
Back of a length, on middle. Liton Das stands tall and blocks it out.
Short ball, on middle. Liton Das looks to pull but misses and gets hit on the arm.
Nearly played on! Length ball, on off. Nurul Hasan looks to defend but gets an inside edge. The ball rolls back to the keeper.
Beauty! Length ball, around off, nipping away. Nurul Hasan looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length ball, around off, nipping away. Nurul Hasan leaves it alone.
FOUR! Edgy but Bangladesh won't mind it. Fuller, outside off. Nurul Hasan reaches out for it and looks to drive. The ball goes off the outside edge over the gully fielder for a boundary.
Similar line and length on off. Nurul Hasan is solid in his defence.
On a good length, on off. Nurul Hasan blocks it out from the crease.
Fuller, outside off. Liton Das leaves it for the keeper to collect.
FOUR! Pulled away and in the gap! Short of a length, on middle. Liton Das pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Lovely shot that.
On a length, on middle. Liton Das defends it back to the bowler.
Length ball, outside off. Liton Das lets it sail through.
On a length, on middle. Liton Das defends it out.
Short again, outside off. Liton Das tries to pull but misses.
Short ball from Wagner, on off. Nurul Hasan swivel-pulls it to deep square leg for a single. Neil Wagner will have to reload as he has overstepped. No ball called.
Inside edge there! Length ball, on off, coming back in. Liton Das looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Big appeal from Tim Southee for an lbw but nothing from the umpire.
Fuller in length, outside off. Liton Das presses forward and defends it towards covers.
Length ball, on off. Liton Das defends it out.
On a good length, outside off, swinging away. Liton Das leaves it untouched.
Good-length ball again, around the fifth stump this time. Left alone.
Good-length ball but wide outside off. Not played at.
A short one, this is pulled down to fine leg for one.

That is a snorter! Have to say, it is well played in the end by Das! A sharp bumper on middle, Das initially looks to defend but then realizes it is a little too quick. He gets his hands out of the way and lets it through to the keeper.
Short again, Nurul helps it on its way down to fine leg for one more.
Shorter again and on off, Hasan stands tall and blocks it.
Shorter and on middle, Das pulls, it goes towards deep square leg for one.
A short one, Das looks to pull but misses. There is half an appeal from the keeper but nothing.
Uppish but just wide! This one tails back in from off, Hasan gets his front leg out of the way and works it uppishly but wide of mid-wicket and to mid on.
Fuller again, this one tails back in from outside off, Hasan looks to drive but it goes off the inner half on the leg side.
Shorter and on off, this is guided to gully.
That is close! Boult gets this to come back in from outside off, Hasan did plant his front foot a little too across but connects with his bat and plays it to mid off.
Length and on off, Das pushes it through covers. Three taken. That was not a bad ball, it was hit on the up through covers.
That is a beauty! Length and on off, this lands and then moves away. Das is beaten as he tries to block.
Goes length now and on off, defended.
Nicely played! Shorter and on middle, Hasan gets on top of the bounce and keeps it out on the off side.
Nurul Hasan walks out to bat!

OUT! TAKEN! Wagner has another one and New Zealand now are managing to take wickets at regular intervals. They are just 5 wickets away now. Yasir Ali, who was quite solid in the first innings, falls to a nasty nut from Wagner. It is short and on the body, Yasir looks to fend it away again but does so uncomfortably. It goes off the splice and lobs to Latham at second slip. He takes a dolly. You just can't do a lot about such deliveries, you know they are coming but can't do a lot about it. Wagner is pumped and roaring in delight.
Commentary.Howout: c Tom Latham b Neil Wagner

Commentary.Commentary: Shorter and on middle, this is pulled through square leg for one.
Drop and run! On off, Ali pushes it towards cover for one.
Good length and on off, defended. Wagner oversteps, probably trying too hard for that extra yard of pace.
A short one, Ali quite nervously ducks under it.
On middle, kept out.
Fuller and on off, this is pushed towards mid off for one.
On middle, Yasir plays it to mid-wicket.
A short one on middle, ducked under.
On middle, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
Fuller and on middle, this is driven to mid on.

It is all happening out there! Not sure how Ali has not been dismissed! This is a nasty delivery, it is short and on the body, Ali looks to fend it away. It hits the glove and lobs behind over the slip cordon. Nicholls and Latham both go for it. The former from gully and the latter from second slip. Nicholls leaps and looks to take it with one hand but it does not stay in. Ali goes for a run but is sent back. Taylor picks the ball up and then has a shy at the keeper's end but misses. Yasir may have been short. In the end though he survives. Maybe Nicholls should have left it for Latham, it could have been an easier chance for him. No one called but there wasn't much time to call, to be honest.
Goes short now and on the body, ducked under.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Taylor holds onto it and this time there is no doubt. Haque departs. He always seemed uncomfortable with those deliveries outside off. He chased quite a few and missed quite a few, a couple of edges were also found which did not go to hand but his luck runs out this time. Wagner goes full and outside off, a litltle bit of shape away. Haque goes after it, it goes off the outside edge and it is taken by Taylor at first slip. New Zealand 6 wickets away now.
Commentary.Howout: c Ross Taylor b Neil Wagner

Commentary.Commentary: Shorter and on the pads, this is nudged on the leg side.
Fuller and on off, Haque plays it to covers.
Shorter and down the leg side. Left alone.
Edged and taken! Das reviews. He indicates it's off the arm.

NOT OUT! It indeed is off the shoulder! Good review by Das and he survives. Excellent delivery from Boult though. He kept getting the ball back in but this time bangs it shorter and angles it away from off. Das is squared up as he tries to block. It seems to have gone off the edge to the keeper who takes it. The umpire raises his finger. Das reviews and replays show the on-field call has to be overturned.
Outside off, Das leaves it alone.
On middle, Das is solid in defense.
Shorter and on off, Das guides it to point.
Fuller and on off, this is pushed to mid off.
Gets this one to tail back in from off. Das works it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! Edgy. Wagner gets a length ball to nip away from around off and Mominul has a tame poke inside the line. The outside edge flies wide of Tom Latham at second slip, and goes through the vacant third slip region for a boundary.
Short again, that is flicked away but straight to the fielder at backward square leg.
Shortish and around middle, eased behind square leg for two.
Another bumper, angling down the leg side, Mominul has nothing to do with it. Wide given.
Bouncer, the batsman ducks under that one.
Short around leg, pulled down to fine leg for a run.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Fuller and outside off, left alone.
Another leave as another delivery is bowled outside off.
Yet another ball outside off, not played at.
Outside off, left alone.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for two.

Drinks. Another hour of exciting action has passed! Bangladesh showed positive intent in the afternoon session but a screamer of a catch by Tom Latham ended Mohammad Naim's stay. Mominul has worked hard after a nervy start and along with Liton Das, his plan would be to form a big partnership. Can he succeed?
Angling away from around off, Das stays back and plays it down defensively to point.
A touch short and around off, defended off the back foot.
Around off on a length, the batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Another short ball down the leg side, Das shoulders arms.
Better line, short and around off, leaving the batter with the angle, Das drops his hands and leans back to evade it.
Begins his spell with a short delivery but it's down the leg side, Liton leaves.
Another bowling change. Neil Wagner to operate.
A little too full on this occasion, around off, Das drives through covers for three runs.
Back of a length, around off, defended off the back foot.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Short and around off, from around the stumps, Das drops his wrists and allows it through.
Das leans forward and across before pushing a full ball to mid on.
Right on the money, as always. Lands it full and around off, shaping in, Das is forward in defense.
Trent Boult to bowl now.
Fuller and on off, Mominul plays late and pushes it away off the outer half to cover-point.
Well wide outside off, on a length, an easy leave.
Fullish and on off, it's driven without much timing towards mid off.
Uses the angle of the bowler and helps it towards square leg.
Fuller this time, outside off, this time the Bangla skipper covers his stumps with his big stride forward and makes a leave.
A near drag-on! Around off on a length, Mominul gets forward and pushes at it. The ball gathers the inside edge and goes closely past the stumps to the keeper.
Good fielding! Fuller and on off, Das drives but the man at covers dives to his right and stops it.
On off, this is pushed down the ground towards mid off for one.
FOUR! Over the top! It goes off the shoulder. Shortish and on off, this one takes off. Haque looks to defend but it goes off the shoulder, over the slip cordon and into the third man fence.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
Fuller and outside off, easy leave.
Outside off, length, left alone.
A dot to end a successful over! On a length and around off, blocked.
Yet another outswinger but the line is outside off. Left alone again.
Lovely nut! Fuller and it shapes away, the line though is a little outside off. Left alone.
Two bouncers in a row now! Das lets it go over him.
Shorter in length and on middle, a bumper to welcome the new batter. Evaded.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Finally the edge is found and it goes to hand! Not exactly to hand as it is a catch manufactured and what a grab it is. Tom Latham, you beauty! That is a screamer. Wow! Southee manages to break the stand that was going along nicely. This catch will lift the Kiwis. Southee persists with the line outside off. This is fuller and it is the tempter. Naim falls for it and goes for the drive. This flies off the outside edge to the left of Latham at second slip who dives and takes it behind him. Naim's gritty little innings comes to an end. Das walks out to bat now.
Commentary.Howout: c Tom Latham b Tim Southee

Commentary.Commentary: A dot to end! A harmless delivery outside off, easy leave.
Nicely played! Runs coming thick and fast! On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket. Three taken.
Good shot but for no runs! Shorter and on off, Naim pushes it to covers.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Another play and a miss! This is a loose shot. Full and well wide outside off, Haque looks to drive but is beaten.
Just outside off, a back-of-a-length ball. Left alone.
Three more and that brings the 100 up! Fuller and outside off, this is driven. Through covers for three.
Beaten! Frustrating stuff for the Kiwis. The outside edges aren't finding the fielder and the good deliveries aren't finding the edge. Fuller and outside off, Haque looks to drive but is beaten.
More runs, this time for Haque! On the pads, it is clipped through mid-wicket for two.
Southee goes full now. Naim just uses the pace and pushes it through covers. Three taken. Trail below 300 now.
On the pads, Naim flicks but to mid-wicket.
Two more! On middle, Naim works it through mid-wicket for two.
Left on length again. Good stuff. Outside off, Haque shoulders arms to it. It goes over the off pole.

FOUR! Edged and it goes over. Luck favouring Bangladesh at the moment. This is full and outside off. Mominul Haque looks to drive, he goes hard at it. This flies off the outside edge and over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Two! Good running! Angled into the pads, it is worked through square leg for a couple.
On middle, Haque works it to the man at short leg.
Back of a length again and outside off, coming in with the angle. Left on length.
Shortish and outside off, left alone.
Three taken! Fuller and on off, this is driven down towards long off. Three ran with ease.
This time he gets right behind the line of the delivery and keeps it out.
Twice in a row now! Southee gets it to tail back in from wide outside off. Haque is beaten again as he looks to defend.
Beaten! And again, Haque plays inside the line of a delivery which is just outside off, worried about it swinging back in. Beaten.
On the stumps again, Haque keeps it out.
On off, defended.
Angled into the pads, this is worked on the leg side for one.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed to covers for one.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.
Angled into the off pole, blocked.
Good length and on off, Naim pushes it to covers.
Beaten again! Another delivery on a length and just outside off. Haque plays for the delivery coming into him. He ends up playing inside the line and is beaten.
Beauty! This is on a length and around off, holds its line. Haque looks to defend but is beaten.
Lands it full and around off, Mominul is forward a bit as he eases it to covers.
On off, Haque pushes it to covers.
Close! Fuller and this one comes back in from outside off. Haque looks to play but it goes off the inner half on the leg side.
Good length and on middle, defended.
Wagner is back on the field now.
On off, defended.
Just short. Naim, all of a sudden, does not look comfortable here. Shorter and on middle, Naim looks to play the pull, it hits the inside edge, then the pads but lands short of the short leg fielder.
Close! Just outside off and comes in with the angle. Naim does not cover his off pole and tries to leave. Goes close past the off pole.
BEATEN AGAIN! Length and just outside off, Naim looks to defend probably due to the around the wicket angle, he is beaten.
On middle, blocked.
Good start by Kyle! Length and on off from around the wicket. This lands and then holds its line. Naim looks to defend but is beaten.

Who will bowl from the other end? Before that though the 4th official comes out to the middle and gives a tablet to one of the umpires. Kyle Jamieson to bowl. Let's hope all's well with Boult and Wagner and they don't stay indoors for long.
Fuller and on off, this is pushed to mid off.
Another length ball on off, a little bit of inward movement. Defended.
Back of a length and on off, Haque stays back and keeps it out.
More runs! Length and on off, Haque pushes it through covers for two.
Now gets this one to shape back in from off. Corrects his line and length. Defended.
FOUR! A loosener to begin with! On the pads, Haque works it fine and this one races away to the fence.
Time for the action to begin! Mohammad Naim and Mominul Haque will resume their innings. Wagner and Boult have not come on the field after the break. Tim Southee to begin. Here we go...
... Day 3, Session 2 ...

It's been a much-better show from the touring team in the second dig but in the context of this Test match, they are still way behind the 8-ball. Bangladesh have taken a baby step to stay relevant and they will have to keep doing that to keep New Zealand at bay. Mominul Haque has had a nervy start to his innings, surviving a run out chance and also nearly handing a simple catch to short leg in his 5-ball stay at the crease. His presence will be important for Bangladesh to blunt the Kiwi attack. Do join us in a short while at 6.10 am IST (12.40 am GMT) for the afternoon session.

End of an absorbing morning session. Bangladesh almost had a session to their name in this Test match. After seeing their performance with the bat on Day 2, we were expecting that New Zealand will blow them away after enforcing the follow-on but that's not the case. The Bangla openers showed better resolve and character, and the hosts had to sweat hard in the first hour. Just at the stroke of the Drinks break this morning, Kyle Jamieson strangled Shadman Islam down the leg side and would have removed Najmul Hossain Shanto too had Daryl Mitchell not dropped the catch in the slip cordon. Minutes before the Lunch break though, Neil Wagner brought his trademark short deliveries into play to bounce out Shanto to make it an even session for both teams.
Negotiated well! On the off pole, Naim defends it onto the ground. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3!
Outside off, left alone. One ball to go before the break.
A sharp bumper, Naim lets it go over him.
Close! Good length and on off, this one lands and jags back in. Naim looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Good shot! On middle, Naim plays it to mid on.
Some nice swing for Boult! The line is outside off, left alone.
Good-length delivery to end, Haque gets right behind the line and plays it to mid off. Solid defensive stroke.
Another short one and on middle, Haque evades it by ducking.
That was not far away! Shorter and on the body, Haque flicks, it goes uppishly but past short leg.
NO BALL! Wagner has overstepped. Short and on middle, Haque ducks under it.

Direct hit and Mominul Haque was a goner! Daryl Mitchell fails to take another opportunity which comes to him. He probably had more time than he thought. Fuller and on middle, Haque pushes it towards mid on and takes off. There is no run in it. Mitchell runs to the ball, picks it up and then looks to underarm it onto the stumps at the bowler's end but misses. It goes past the fielder backing up and another run is taken. Had he hit, Mominul Haque was not even in the frame.

OUT! TAKEN! It is Wagner who comes out on top in his battle with Shanto! He is pumped up and that is yet another good catch, this time by Boult and New Zealand have a wicket a few minutes before Lunch. Just what they would have wanted. The barrage of short balls works. Shanto got a few runs from the pull shot but Wagner continues to bang it in. Shanto pulls again, this time flat and towards Boult. It goes to him at fine leg quickly but he hangs on. Can New Zealand take another one before the break? Still a little time left. Mominul Haque walks out to bat.
Commentary.Howout: c Trent Boult b Neil Wagner

Commentary.Commentary: Goes short and on the body, Shanto hops and works it on the leg side.

Almost plays it on! Length and on middle, this one skids through. Naim hangs back and looks to defend, gets his bat down a little late. It hits the underedge, hits the pad and almost rolls onto the stumps behind.
Goes fuller, Boult actually tries the yorker, this one though ends up being a low full toss, it also swings back in. This is worked to mid-wicket.
Back of a length and on off, Naim hangs back and plays it to point.
On middle, Naim plays it to mid on.
Just outside off, Naim shoulders arms to this one.
On middle, Naim plays it late and onto the ground. He played that right under his eyes.
A bumper to end, Shanto ducks under it. A good over for Bangladesh.
Another one on the shorter side, Shanto rides on top of the bounce and defends.
Goes short despite being hit for two boundaries. Defended.
FOUR! And again, this is hit even harder! Shorter in length, Shanto pulls it with control through square leg. Boundary again.
FOUR! Nailed behind square leg! There are two fielders at the back but Shanto does not care. He pulls this short one very hard and into the gap for a boundary.
Another short one, Shanto defends.
Attacks the stumps this time, Naim blocks.
Just outside off again, Naim watches it closely and lets it go through to the keeper.
On the fuller side now and outside off, left alone.

FOUR BYES! That just took off! Down the leg side, Naim misses the flick, it takes off and swings down the leg further. The keeper dives to his right and tries to take it with one hand, it hits the fingers and goes down to fine leg for a boundary.
Yet another loose stroke by Naim! Shorter and outside off, Naim flays at it but is beaten.
Angled into the pads, Naim works it towards square leg. Daryl Mitchell there dives to his left and stops it.
Manages to keep it down! End of an entertaining over! Shorter and on the body, Shanto looks to nudge it on the leg side but it hits the glove and rolls towards leg gully.
Yet anotehr short ball and on the body, Shanto ducks under it.
Shorter and on middle, Shanto works it to mid-wicket. This is a good contest between the two. Shanto winning it for now.
FOUR! Between the keeper and leg gully! This will only frustrate Wagner. On the body, Shanto works it fine, past the keeper and into the fine leg fence.
TOP EDGE AND SIX! That flies all the way! Short and on the body, Shanto looks to pull, it goes off the top edge but flies over the fine leg fence. 50 up for Bangladesh. Still a long way to go.
On the shorter side, Shanto stands tall and plays it onto the ground.
FOUR! Short and wide and put away! That is a hit-me ball! It sits up to be hit, Naim plays it through covers and it races away to the fence.
On middle, Naim pushes it to mid on.
Another nut not on the stumps, easy leave.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, defended.
Down the leg side, Naim looks to flick but misses.
Goes short again, Shanto rides on top of the bounce and defends it onto the ground.
Nicely played again! On the body, Shanto hops and works it along the ground to the fielder at leg gully.
Yet another short one on middle, Shanto hangs back and plays it down onto the ground.
Back of a length and on off, Shanto hangs back and defends.
Another quick short ball, Shanto ducks under it.
Shorter and on the body, Shanto plays it well, he hops and nudges it to short leg.
The around the wicket angle almost does the trick, this is quite wide outside off, the around the wicket angle though is the reason Naim has a push at it, he does so away from his body. Gets beaten.
Yet another fuller delivery on off, Naim pushes it to covers.
Goes full and wide outside off, wanting the batter to go for a drive. It is left alone.
Length and on off, Naim pushes it on the up but can't get it past mid off.
On the pads, Naim looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Left on length! Slightly shorter than a length, Naim leaves it alone. It goes over the off pole.
Wagner falls onto the ground in his followthrough! Maybe trying to hard! Length and on off, Shanto defends it.
The rib-tickler this time, Naim works it down to fine leg and gets to the other end.
Make that three in a row! This one is well-directed. It is well played by Naim as he just sways out of the way again.
Two bumpers in a row, this time a lot straighter, ducked under.
A good short one now, Naim though evades it well.
On middle, Naim hangs back and keeps it out.
On middle, Shanto plays it back to the bowler.
Another good leave! Just outside off, Shanto does not fiddle with it.
Outside off, Shanto leaves it alone.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
FOUR! Shanto has started aggressively here! Fuller and on off, this is hit down to the long off fence for a boundary.
Shorter and on middle, Shanto defends it onto the ground.
Quick run! On middle, this is worked to mid on. The batters take off. Boult gets to the ball, picks it up but can't get his balance, he is late in throwing it and the batter is well in.
A loud appeal but turned down! Going down leg! Full and on the pads, Shanto looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Really good shot! Back of a length and on off, Naim stands tall and pushes it through covers for three.
Just a mere push! On middle, Naim hits it past the bowler. Boult, at mid on, hares after it and keeps it down to two.
Slightly fuller and on off, Naim pushes it to mid off.
On middle, defended. Wagner has overstepped. No ball signaled.
Good delivery, length and on off, shapes away. Defended.
Fuller and on middle, Shanto strokes it towards mid on. The fielder dives to his left and stops it.

EDGED AND PUT DOWN! Daryl Mitchell it is! He should not have gone for it! A shortish delivery outside off, Shanto pushes at it with hard hands away from his body and this flies off the outside edge. It seems to be going straight to Tom Latham at second slip but Daryl Mitchell, at third slip, dives to his right and tries with one hand but it does not stay in and goes behind for a couple of runs. Kyle Jamieson could have had his second.
Close! Length and on off, Shanto looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Goes short now and on the body, Shanto ducks under it.
FOUR! Off the mark in style! Full and on middle, Shanto clips it brilliantly through mid-wicket and this one races away to the fence.
Good length and on off, Shanto blocks.
A maiden by Wagner! On middle, Naim works it to mid-wicket.
On off, Naim pushes it but to covers.
On middle, blocked.
Down the leg side, Naim leaves it alone.
On the stumps, kept out.
Fuller and on off, this is pushed to mid off.
Fuller and outside off, Shanto does not fiddle with it! End of a wicket-taking over by Kyle.

Drinks. A wicket against the run of play and New Zealand managed to finish the first hour with a wicket. The Bangla openers looked a lot assured and showed the correct temperament and technique to deal with the new ball. A complete contrast to the first innings and it seems that the Kiwi bowlers will have to work a lot harder to create breakthroughs. The first hour still has belonged to the tourists, let's see who takes the cake in the next hour.
Najmul Hossain Shanto is the new batsman.

OUT! TAKEN! That is a superb catch by Tom Blundell! Kyle Jamieson gets the breakthrough New Zealand wanted. They had to wait for quite some time for the first wicket as compared to the first innings but they finally have got it. Shadman Islam falls in a very soft manner. He will be gutted with himself. This is down the leg side, he looks to flick but his bottom hand comes off the handle in the process. It goes off the fine edge to the right of Tom. He dives and takes a one-handed spectacular catch. Shadman Islam walks back slowly, he was playing really well till then. Walks back after getting off to a start. Will this open the floodgates now?
Commentary.Howout: c Tom Blundell b Kyle Jamieson

Commentary.Commentary: On off again, Islam pushes it to covers.
On off, drags the length back, blocked.
FOUR! Put away nicely! Full and outside off, Islam strokes it through covers. This one races away to the fence.
Outside off, shapes away. Islam does not play at it.
Angled into the pads, Islam works it through square leg and takes one.
On off, Islam defends.
Solid this time! On off and on a length, defended.
Really good stuff! Makes the batter play again and lands it on off, shapes away a little. Islam looks to defend but this one too goes off the outer half to point.
Fuller again, gets it to shape away, Islam pushes it to covers.
Begins right on the money! Fuller and on off, this one shapes away. Islam looks to defend but it goes more off the outer half to point.
Neil Wagner is on now!
A harmless nut to end! Down the leg side, left alone.
Fuller and on middle, Naim works it to mid-wicket.
On the pads, Islam looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls on the leg side. A leg bye taken.
On the pads, this is clipped through square leg for one.
Goes fuller this time and on middle, Islam works it through mid-wicket for one.
Back of a length, gets it to shape away nicely from around leg, defended.
Good leave to end the over! Just outside off, Naim shoulders arms to this one.
BEATEN! Lovely delivery! This lands on off and then moves away this time, it goes the other way, Naim looks to defend but is beaten.
Nicely played again! On middle, with the swing, Naim clips it through mid-wicket for two.
Goes fuller and gets it to tail back in from off, Naim pushes it to mid off.
Good running! On off, this is pushed towards the right of the mid off fielder for one.
The openers have been quite assured so far! Outside off, Islam covers his off pole and leaves it alone.
A dot to end! On middle, Naim plays it towards the leg side.
Well bowled and well left! This one begins around middle and off and shapes away. Naim lets it be.
Shorter and on middle, Naim works it to mid-wicket.
Solid! On middle, Naim plays it right under his eyes.
Back of a length and on off, Naim stands tall and defends.
Extra bounce for Kyle Jamieson! Shorter and on middle, this one angles away. Naim does well to drop his hands and lets it go to the keeper.
Change! Kyle Jamieson is on now!
On off, Islam pushes it to covers.

Some aggression from Southee! Fuller and on off, this one swings back in. The batter gets his front pad out of the way and plays it back to Southee! He mimes to throw it back at the keeper's end but does not. Gives the batter a stare too.
Back of a length and on off, Islam guides it to point.
A good bumper, on middle, Islam ducks under it.
Two more! Shorter and on off, this is pushed through covers for two.
FOUR! Bangladesh move onto 14, they were 4 down in the first innings by now but have not lost a wicket yet. Fuller and on off, Islam leans into it and drives it through covers. Races away.
Outside off, left alone.
Almost finds the edge! First real poor shot from one of the Bangladesh openers. Fuller and on off, shapes away late. Naim looks to drive with no foot movement. He gets beaten.
Nicely played! On middle, Naim hangs back and blocks it onto the ground.
On the pads, Islam works it through mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Just outside off, Islam walks across and leaves it alone.
The Bangladesh openers have looked in no trouble whatsoever! Length and on off, Islam plays it to covers.
A dot to end! Well outside off, easy leave.
Gets it to shape back in but the line is on the pads, Naim looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Well left! Outside off and on a length, left alone.
Bangs it short and on middle, Naim ducks under it.
Good length, this one tails back in from outside off. Blocked.
The tempter by Southee! Full and well wide outside off, left alone.
Nicely played! Fuller and outside off, Islam lunges, with the movement, he plays it to covers.
Naim takes one now! Length and on off, this one moves away. Naim looks to defend but it goes off the outer half through point for one.
Pulled nicely! First run off Boult in this innings! Shorter and on the body, this is pulled down to fine leg for one.
On middle, Islam flicks it to mid on.
This one shapes away! The line is well wide outside off, left alone.
Needed to get bat on that! On middle, Islam plays it with his bat in front of the bat. Had he missed that, he was out plumb LBW.
Plays at one he could have left. Outside off, Naim pokes at it, it goes off the under-edge on the off side.
Right off the middle again, the confidence of the Bangladesh openers will grow now! On off, this is pushed to mid off. They have not looked in any kind of trouble.
Well played! Southee goes fuller, this one comes back in from outside off, Naim plays it with the swing to mid on.
Another one on a length and around off, Naim stays back and blocks it.
A lot closer to the off pole this time, Naim is in two minds whether to leave or play, in the end, he looks to defend but gets an under-edge behind the wickets.
Southee now comes from around the wicket, he shapes it back in a long way but it is still wide outside off. Left alone.
A good delivery to end! Another over played without any fuss! Fuller and on off, Islam defends it on the off side.
Three leaves in a row now! Outside off, not played at.
This time it is a lot closer to the off pole and goes on with the angle. Islam though covers his off pole and lets it go to the keeper.
Yet another delivery which shapes away but the line is well outside off, easy leave.
Really well bowled! This one shapes away nicely, the line though is a touch outside off. Islam looks to defend but he is beaten by a long way.
Gets this one to shape away! Islam shoulders arms to this one.
Nicely played then! Shorter and on middle, Islam hops and works it on the leg side for one. The first three overs were negotiated quite easily by the openers.
Bowls fuller this time and on off, Islam pushes it to mid off.
Played nicely for one and Naim is off the mark! Fuller and on the pads, he clips it through square leg and gets to the other end.
Southee now angles this one away but the line is from outside off, left alone.
Really solid! Length and on off, Naim plays it late and right under his eyes on the off side.
On middle, Naim works it to mid-wicket.
A solid defensive stroke to end the over! A maiden to begin with by Boult! On off, Islam plays it to mid off.
A short one now, Islam looks to cut but there is not enough room to play that shot. He chops it to covers.
Goes fuller and tries to shape it away from the leg pole, not a lot of movement this time, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Good length and on off, Islam stays back and keeps it out.
Good length and on off, Islam this time defends it right off the middle.
Right on the money to begin with! Length and on off, he gets it to shape away. He also gets some extra bounce. It goes off the outside edge but well short of gully.
Trent Boult to bowl from the other end. He got a fifer in the first innings, would love another one here.
A good start then by Bangladesh! On the pads, Naim works it to square leg.
Solid! On off, Naim gets behind the line and blocks.
And again, brings it back in to the left-hander. On the stumps, Shadman pushes it past the bowler for one.
This one starts from well outside off, shapes back in. Does not come in enough to make the batter play.
Gets the line right this time! Southee goes full and he tails it back in from outside off, Islam looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Half an appeal but turned down.

FOUR! Bangladesh and Shadman are underway! Some shape and bounce for Southee! Slightly shorter in length and it starts on middle, this one tails back in. Extra bounce too. Islam looks to flick, it takes the glove and goes past the diving keeper and down to the fine leg fence.
